title: eggnog cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk, rum, shortening, nutmeg and ginger together on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 3 minutes, scraping bowl frequently. Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is done. Cool completely before frosting.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Can add more marshmallows and add 1 cup chopped walnuts.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine dates, brown sugar, water and butter in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until dates soften.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate morsels.
Beat in eggs, then add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and milk.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan (jelly pan) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: sloppy joe pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust and spread on greased pan.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Spread barbecue sauce on crust. Spread ground beef on sauce; next, a layer of corn and layer of sauce.
Top whole pizza with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla chip maple cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the shortening, butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla and maple flavoring.
Combine the flour and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of the tomato soup with the rest of the ingredients.
Shape into balls (1 1/2-inch).
Brown in 2 tablespoons of shortening with 1 small garlic clove (minced) in skillet.
Blend in rest of can of soup and 1 cup of water.
Cover. Simmer about 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull the chicken off
the
bone
and
place chunks in a large bowl.
Mix in
the mushroom soup, which has been thinned with the broth, the
rice,
onion,
salt and pepper.
Pour all into
a greased
baking dish and cover with the bread crumbs. Melt
the stick
of butter and pour over the casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until browned and bubbling.

title: hot chicken salad(servings:  8)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Line 3-quart Pyrex with crushed potato chips.
Add chicken mixture and top with grated cheese and more crushed chips.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Into a large bowl, sift together flour, salt, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, vegetable oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple.
Mix well by hand.
Don't use electric mixer! Fold in bananas and nuts. Pour into a greased, floured baking tin or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown beef and pour off fat.
Combine all ingredients and pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mee maw's chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks, add part of milk.
Sift together sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add to yolk mixture stirring well.
Cook on medium heat. Add remainder of milk, butter and water, cook until thick.
Stir frequently to keep filling smooth.
Pour into baked shell. Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: tuna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine all of the above ingredients, mixing well.
In a casserole dish, put mixture in and top off with additional 1/2 cup of bread crumbs and a pat of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add grits, Lawry's salt and salt.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese, oleo and Tabasco sauce. Cook on low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add eggs.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: overnight buns
directions: At 6:00 p.m., combine all ingredients.
Mix and punch down at 8:00.
Make into rolls at 10:00.
Let raise until morning.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen buns.

title: best burritos
directions: Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning and water.
Let simmer. Heat refried beans and warm tortilla shells.
Mix tomato sauce with taco sauce and spread 3/4 cup of this mix on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside the rest of sauce mixture.
Fill each tortilla shell with 1/3 cup each of cheese, meat mix and beans.
Fold shells burrito-style and line them up in pan.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Before serving, spread sour cream on top.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Boil for 2 minutes (be careful not to scorch); remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool and beat until frosting reaches consistency for spreading.

title: oven stew
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir every hour until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: baked lamb chops
directions: Line large baking dish with sauerkraut; place chops on top of sauerkraut.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with brown sugar. Gently pour water in along side of pan.
Cover and bake in a 325° for 3 hours or until chops are tender.

title: magic cookie barshouston, texas
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350° if using a metal 13 X 9 pan, 325° if using a glass one.
Combine crumbs with butter and press into bottom of pan.
Pour condensed milk over the crumb mixture.
Add the second layer by pressing the coconut over the top of the crumb/condensed milk.
Layer the chocolate chips next.
End with a layer of walnuts.
Press entire mix down.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until the coconut is lightly browned.
Let the pan cool for 1 to 2 hours, then cut into bars.

title: tiger stripes
directions: Line an 8 x 8 inch square pan with foil; grease.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with 2 Tbsp. chunky peanut butter over low heat in a small sauce pan; stir well.
Pour half of chocolate mixture into prepared pan.
Let stand 10 -15 minutes to cool slightly.
Melt white chocolate baking bars with remaining 1 Tbsp. peanut butter over low heat in a small sauce pan.
Spoon half of the white chocolate mixture over dark chocolate mixture.
Drop remaining dark and white chocolate mixture by spoonfuls over mixture in pan.
Using a small metal spatula knife, pull through the chocolate to make tiger stripes.
Freeze about 1 hour or until firm.
Remove from pan, peel off foil, cut into 36 pieces. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 36 squares.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
(Crack ice cubes before dropping in the blender, if your blender directions so state.) Blend thoroughly and serve immediately.

title: pork chop delite
directions: In skillet, add butter and brown chops; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Layer vegetables in crock pot and top with chops.
Mix soup and water together.
Add worcestershire sauce and pour over chops.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: taco tower
directions: Mix in small bowl, mashed avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix together in second small bowl, sour cream, mayonnaise and Taco seasoning mix.
Layer all ingredients in a 9 inch x 13 inch dish starting with the bean dip (or refried beans) and ending with the Mexican blended cheese.
Order of layer:
Bean dip, Avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, olives, onions, and cheese.

title: horseradish dressing(low-cal)
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve mustard with 1 tablespoon water. Add the rest of the ingredients and beat well. Serve over fish, meats, vegetables or salads.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain off fat.
Mix together beaten eggs, milk, salt, mustard.
Break up bread, add cheese and sausage.
Pour into a greased glass baking dish (11 x 7-inch).
Refrigerate overnight. Marvelous brunch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Set aside.
Slice ice cream in eighths, it's easier to slice into halves and then slice each half into half and so on.

title: eggplant margarita
directions: Put all ingredients except eggplant into a frying pan.
Bring to a boil and let simmer until sauce has thickened.
Place 1/2 teaspoon butter or margarine on sheet pan.
Lay out eggplant and top with ingredients from frying pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine the first 9 ingredients.
Blend together remaining ingredients and toss with vegetable mixture. Chill.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: creamy pasta florentine
directions: In large pot, cook fettuccine as directed.
Add spinach to water during last 4 minutes of cooking time.
Drain fettuccine and spinach in a colander.
In same pot, over medium heat, combine water, cheese, bouillon and nutmeg; Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Add fettuccine and spinach; mix well.
Garnish with toasted bread crumbs and grated parmesan cheese if desired.
Makes 6 - 1 cup servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, slightly beaten eggs, flour, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nifty green beans
directions: In skillet over medium gas flame, fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Crumble.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon. Saute celery and onion in reserved fat over medium gas flame. Add beans and dill; heat.
Add processed cheese spread; turn off flame.
Stir until cheese spread begins to melt.
Top with bacon. Yield:
6 servings.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients. Toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan. Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shell according to package directions and drain.
Mix in larger bowl, remaining ingredients except the spaghetti sauce. Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with 1 cup sauce.
Fill each shell with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining sauce and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Slice apples in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Use generous amount of apples.
Fill about 1/2 full.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and pour apple juice over apples.
Cook until bubbly and hot thoroughly. Cut brown bread in 3 pieces.
Remove crust.
Pour over apples evenly.
Mix egg, melted margarine, flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and lemon flavoring.
Mix ingredients and pour over bread slices.
Bake at 370° until golden brown.

title: herb parmesan bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese,
onion
flakes, oregano and 3 cups of flour. Beat until blended	and
smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add rest of flour or enough
to make a stiff dough.
Knead, adding flour until smooth and not
sticky.
Let
rise in a warm place 45 minutes or until
doubled
in	bulk.
Punch
down dough and knead a few minutes.
Lightly
grease one 2 quart casserole or 2 loaf pans. Turn
into	containers,
butter
top lightly and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon	Parmesan
cheese.
Let rise again and bake in a
375° oven
preheated
for
minutes
(large casserole) or 30 to 40 minutes
loaf
pans)
until nicely browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Serve warm.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Set aside half of this mixture; press remaining mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend granulated sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk and lemon juice; beat well.
Pour over prebaked mixture. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool, then refrigerate.
When chilled, cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Follow jello box directions for pudding instead of pie. (Makes the pie fuller.)
Pour into crust.
Icing with cool whip.
I like to put chocolate slices or some kind of candy on top of cool whip.
Refrigerate.

title: baked sweet potatoes with ginger butter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Scrub unpeeled sweet potatoes; rub with vegetable oil. Pierce in several places with a fork and wrap in foil. Place directly on rack. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut a crosswise gash in top of each potato. In a bowl, beat butter with ginger until fluffy. Spoon into a serving bowl. Serve over sweet potatoes. Serves 12.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Separate ladyfingers.
Line sides and bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Press in firmly.
Set aside.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil until sugar is well mixed.
Add tea bags and let stand until cool.
Add brandy, orange juice and lemonade to mixture and mix well.
Pour into quart containers and freeze.
To serve, spoon into a medium size glass, or, if brave, into a very large glass and add 7-Up to taste.
Keep the unused frozen.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour and place in a greased baking dish.
Top with the remaining ingredients in order as they are listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; cut off ends.
Don't peel.
Cook whole with 1 teaspoon salt in 1-inch boiling water with lid on.
Turn oven to 350°; remove squash from fire.
Cool slightly; cut squash in halves lengthwise.
With spoon, carefully remove squash from shells.
Chop into pieces and combine with rest of ingredients. Use 1/2 cup of cheese in mixture.
Pile into shells; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple dipple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
This makes a stiff batter so beat well.
Fold in chopped apples, Angel Flake coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 1 tube cake or 2 loaf cakes.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: Cook until hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add a few drops of coloring and flavored oil.
Pour into buttered tin. Cool and crack.
Can then be dusted with powdered sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli, then put in buttered pan.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese, then put on bread crumbs and top with drained pimentos.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add to chocolate/butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Best when served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken alfredo(low-fat)
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, blend with wire whisk flour, liquid Butter Buds, skim milk and chicken broth.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook until thickened.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Add cubed chicken.
Fold into cooked pasta. Serve immediately.
If sauce is too thick, can add a little more milk and chicken broth.
Serves 6.
Per Serving:
3.83 g fat and 279 calories.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat and all other ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Return to low heat and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: carrot bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cheese, sour cream, chipped beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce and green pepper in bowl; mix well.
Slice off top of bread.
Cut out soft center carefully, leaving shell.
Spoon cream cheese mixture into bread shell. Replace top.
Bake, wrapped in foil, for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut soft center into cubes.
Serve with dip.

title: punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl and garnish with orange slices.

title: gnocchi (potato balls)
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add egg yolks and 2 tsp. salt, beating well.
Add melted butter. Then, add flour gradually, adding enough so a dough is formed.
Knead dough until smooth. Break off pieces and curl on the tines of a fork.
Add the remaining salt to a large pot of boiling water.
Drop gnocchi into the pot, a few at a time.
When they come to the surface, remove and drain.	Keep warm.
Place in serving dish.
Pour hot tomato sauce over and sprinkle with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Use with round loaf of dark bread, crackers or vegetables.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg, vanilla, oil and baby food.
Blend well.
Add baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.
Do not slice until next day, otherwise cake will crumble.
Keep refrigerated.
Better a few days old.

title: zucchini-raisin bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil in large mixing bowl with mixer at low speed.
Add beaten eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Beat together well.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Put into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out of pans.
May also freeze.

title: meat loaf with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, breaking bread into small pieces before adding.
Shape in casserole or large loaf pan.
Spread cream of mushroom soup, straight from can, on top with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves about 6.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine egg, milk, onions, soup and 3/4 cup herb seasoned stuffing; stir until blended.
Stir in eggplant; spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over casserole; bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no cook mints
directions: Mix together butter, water, flavoring and a few drops of coloring.
Add sugar, enough to make the consistency of pie dough. Press into individual molds or shape into desired shape. Refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve.
Yields about 1 pound.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to a boil; add Jell-O and stir until Jell-O is melted.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk; mix well. Add nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and add grated onion.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
This slaw has a nice tangy taste.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour over melted butter. Do not stir.
Pour pie filling onto mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add self-rising flour and baking soda, then cut bananas up small.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli in undiluted chicken broth.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add flour and stir until thickened. Add salt.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until very thick.
Add to chicken broth and broccoli and mix well.
If you desire, add cheese for added flavor.
Stir until melted.
Serve warm.

title: fettuccini with broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli flowerets in boiling salted water, 2 to 3 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain and keep warm.
Heat oil and butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic, shallot and peppers.
Cook about 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not brown garlic.
Cook pasta in rapidly boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Toss with cheeses.
Put into oiled casserole.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 350° to melt cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kansas city apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello to boiling.
(No extra water is needed.)
Cool in refrigerator until slightly congealed.
Add crumbled cream cheese and beat with electric mixer.
Add celery and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk, vinegar, corn syrup and salt in a greased 5-quart Dutch oven or kettle.
Cook over medium heat to 236° (soft ball stage), stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat. Stir in peanut butter and marshmallow.
When almost blended, add peanuts and vanilla.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil; lightly grease it.
Pour in fudge; refrigerate until completely cooled.
To cut, lift fudge from pan.
Remove foil.
With a large knife, cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
Store in an airtight container in the fridge.

title: custard pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over the bread crumbs.
Cool.
Add butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until very tender.
Let drain through cloth-lined colander or strainer.
Add sugar; stir to dissolve. Add lemon juice.
Chill to serve.

title: refrigerated cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Chill dough.
Divide dough into workable parts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients except the pie crust. Beat for 30 seconds.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until the middle of the pie is set.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni; cool.
Combine all ingredients, except broccoli.
Toss lightly.
Chill several hours.
Add broccoli before serving.
Serves 10 people.

title: fettuccine
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Return to kettle.
Heat butter or margarine with cream, until butter melts.
Pour over noodles. Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss well until noodles are well coated. Serve with salt and pepper and add chunks of cooked chicken if you like.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Cut cheese and butter into small cubes.
Combine with all ingredients and bake in a greased 2-quart baking dish at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Let set about 5 minutes and cut into squares.
Can be cooked ahead of time for 40 minutes, then reheated for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a freezer for at least 24 hours.
Serve frozen.

title: herbed pork tenderloin with oven roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir oil, garlic and seasoning together. Coat meat with 3 tablespoons of seasoning mixture.
Place in large roasting pan.
Toss potatoes with remaining seasoning mixture; arrange around meat in pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: When well blended, pour over vegetables and mix well.

title: butter cake
directions: With mixer, blend until moistened on low speed. Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pat into bottom of 10X15 jelly roll pan. Set aside.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine yeast with water.
Blend 1 package biscuit mix with sugar and oil.
Stir in dissolved yeast.
Cover in refrigerator 1 hour.
Make into rolls.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake in 450° oven 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: broccoli cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat water, 1 teaspoon salt to boiling, stir in macaroni.
Boil until tender 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain, rinse in cold water. Beat egg yolk, stir in macaroni and 1 tablespoon chives. Press mixture against bottom and side of greased 9-inch pie plate with back of spoon.
Bake 10 minutes, remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 425°.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over crust.

title: oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes (or peel); cut into thick strips.
Cover with cold water and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Combine oil, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss well to coat.
Arrange in a single layer on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 475° for 25 minutes or until tender and browned, turning once after 15 minutes.

title: veal scallopini marsala
directions: Place cutlets between waxed paper or foil and pound with side of cleaver until they are about 1/8-inch thick.
Salt and pepper to taste and dredge in flour.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet and brown garlic.
Add veal, cooking over medium heat until brown. Remove veal to shallow baking pan.
Add butter or margarine to skillet and brown mushrooms.
Add Marsala and bring to a boil. Simmer approximately 2 minutes to blend flavors.
Pour wine-mushroom sauce over veal.
Cover pan and bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Blend shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Put dough on floured board.
Knead as little as possible; pat dough, cut and place with sides touching.
Biscuits will be light and fluffy if they are not handled too much.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "cowboy" cheese dip
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until Velveeta melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick company pie
directions: Can use a big can of lemonade and big carton of Cool Whip and make two pies.

title: baked stuffed hamburgers
directions: Put hot water and butter in a bowl.
Stir until butter is melted.
Stir in 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Add stuffing mix; stir until water is absorbed.
Divide meat into 8 parts.
Pat into patties.
Place stuffing on 4 patties, cover with the other 4 patties, then carefully wrap meat around stuffing and seal.
Place in a 9-inch square pan, cover with remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until meat is done.

title: chocolate delite pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press in dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: holiday walnuts
directions: Beat water and egg white until frothy.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and salt together.
Add egg white to nuts.
Stir until nuts are wet.
Add sugar mixture to wet nuts and stir until all are covered.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Store in an airtight container.

title: hot bacon and chicken salad
directions: Combine dressing and mustard; set aside.
Drain grease from just cooked bacon and add oil, mushrooms and onion.
Cook until just tender and remove vegies.
Stir-fry chicken bites.
Re-add vegies and dressing to skillet.
In large bowl place torn greens and bacon and cover with hot mixture.
Top with sliced eggs and serve!

title: garlic or oregano zucchini and tomato broil
directions: Wash zucchini and tomatoes; slices should be between thin and 1/4 inch.
Arrange both vegetables, alternating on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
You may want to boil zucchini a little while to start its cooking (before). Bake-broil at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes, or until tender.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water (1/2 cup) overnight.
Take them out and cover them with boiling water and let set for three hours. Strip cucumbers and put into jar.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, dry mustard and turmeric for sauce.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Boil jars for 5 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine jelly, vinegar, cornstarch and salt. Cook until jelly melts and then until thickened; toss with beans. Add celery and onion.
Let stand for several hours in refrigerator overnight.

title: whipped butter
directions: Mix butter, beating with electric mixer until light and fluffy, then whisking in oil, one tablespoon at a time. Refrigerate in a covered container.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Simmer chicken in
small
amount of water until tender; water should be seasoned with
salt,
pepper and a little dill weed. Combine soup, sour cream, onion, cheese and broth.	Add chicken and bake in
casserole
dish
until
bubbles, about 30 minutes
Serve
over	chow
mein
noodles.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley flakes on top of casserole.
Serves 10.

title: country cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Blend by hand and pour into an 8 x 8 x 2 or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar with fruit (unless fruit was frozen with a sugar syrup).
Pour over batter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: california green bean salad
directions: Steam green beans until tender, yet crisp; cool.
Add onions, bell pepper, shrimp and dressing.
Chill at least 12 hours before serving.
Add pepper and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs, then mix all ingredients together (including the frosting mix).
Bake for 55 minutes in Bundt pan.
Do not open oven door.
Cake falls easily!

title: 1-2-3 biscuits
directions: Stir all ingredients until well blended.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and butter in a saucepan until tender. Stir in cornstarch, wine, parsley, bouillon, salt, water and pepper. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer bottom of casserole dish with asparagus.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over asparagus.
Add cheese.
Melt butter and mix with crumbled crackers.
Place on the cheese layer.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix pecans, flour and softened butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix until smooth the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix until smooth the pudding and milk; pour over filling. Top with Cool Whip, sprinkling nuts on top.
May use any flavor of pudding.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
In a large bowl combine chopped onion, green onion, tomatoes and shredded ham or turkey. Add macaroni and mix with mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste. Put hard-boiled eggs on top.
Eggs can be quartered and laid on top.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cook rice. Add Swiss cheese, butter and soup. Steam mixed vegetables and add to rice all other ingredients. Add chicken breasts. Makes a large casserole dish. Sprinkle bread on top. Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: crock-pot sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage balls in oven about 10 minutes.
Heat jelly, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce mixture.
Add sausage balls and cook in crock-pot for at least 1 hour.

title: cake salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, fruit and nuts.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with foil and freeze overnight.
Can use other fruits, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip in bottom of pie crust.
Freeze 10 minutes.
Carefully spread fudge sauce over whipped cream.
Stir milk gradually into peanut butter until smooth.
Add pudding mix and vanilla.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes; gently stir in remaining Cool Whip.
Carefully spoon over fudge sauce.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until it slices easily.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: chunky peanut brittle
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons of butter. Sprinkle with 1 cup peanut butter chips; set aside. In a heavy saucepan, bring sugar, corn syrup, water and remaining butter to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook and

stir until butter is melted. Cook, without stirring, until a candy thermometer reads 300° (hard-crack stage). Remove from heat; stir in peanuts. Quickly pour onto prepared baking pan; sprinkle with chocolate chips and remaining peanut butter chips. With a knife, gently swirl softened chips over top of brittle. Cool before breaking into pieces. Store in airtight container. Yield: 2 1/2 pounds.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook the shells according to the directions on package.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, egg white, nutmeg and Mozzarella cheese.
Add cooked spinach, steamed.
Stuff the shells with cheese mixture.
Top with Prego and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water for 7 minutes.
Drain. Make sauce of undiluted soup, mayonnaise and curry.
Add nuts. Mix all together.
Place in greased casserole, cover and bake in 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bonbons
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Add flavoring. Gradually add flour and salt.
Pat dough around Kisses (about the size of walnut).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Do not bake more than 12 minutes.)
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bell pepper together.
Then drain off excess grease and add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a casserole dish.

title: squash cheddar bake
directions: In 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 squash.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Fold in whites and cheese.
Crumble bacon on top. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg layer casserole
directions: Place 6 pieces of buttered bread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 sausage and then cover with 1/2 of cheese. Repeat layer one.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers and cover.
Set in refrigerator for at least 3 hours, but best to set overnight.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes about 18.

title: any old fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into one 9 x 13-inch pan and one 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: chicken and barley soup
directions: Put chicken, water and bay leaf in a large pot.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Cool broth and skim off fat.
Bone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Return to pot and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf beforing serving.

title: chicken-bean pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cook chicken in olive oil for 3 minutes until it's not pink.
Add green beans and undrained tomatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 9 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add cheese and pasta and toss.

title: cranberry salad no. 2
directions: Grind together cranberries and orange.
Add sugar; mix jello and hot water.
Cool and then add to first 3 ingredients.
Add celery, nuts and apples.
Chill until firm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, Wesson oil and egg yolks (add one at a time, reserve whites). Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.	Bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to berries.
Fill lined pie shell.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Yields one 9-inch pie.
Raspberries can be used in place of the strawberries in the same quantity.

title: old testament scripture cake
directions: Look up ingredients and fill in.
Mix as any fruit cake.
Bake slowly at 325°, about 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Bake in tube pan.

title: winston caviar(better known as black-eyed pea salad)
directions: Combine all ingredients tossing well to coat thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight. Use as a dip with Frito chips, or eat as a salad.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine broth and rice.
Over medium high heat, heat until boiling.
Cover, cook over low heat 15 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat through stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix the biscuit mix and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk and water in saucepan; heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 1 minute at low speed of mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and continue beating at the same speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Cover batter; let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Stir batter down.
Use hot, greased griddle and about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Makes about 25 pancakes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Cook beef until red is gone; drain. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate all except rye bread.
Cut center out of round rye bread; scoop bread inside out for a bowl.
Break bread into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Just before serving, fill bread bowl with dip.
Place bread pieces around bowl with toothpicks. When dip is gone, eat bread bowl.

title: spaghetti with herb meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: best broccoli soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, bring water to a boil. Add broccoli, celery and carrots. Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Drain; set vegetables aside.

title: jerline's prune cake
directions: Cook and chop prunes.
Blend sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture, alternately with the milk.
Add nuts and prunes; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When done, remove from oven and frost while hot, using Buttermilk Frosting.

title: polish sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Mix sauerkraut, basil and celery seed in 6-cup baking dish. Make deep cuts in sausage, about 1 inch apart.
Push sausage into sauerkraut mixture to cover halfway.
Dissolve brown sugar in hot water and drizzle over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until sausage is tender.

title: pina colada cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolk, pineapple juice and rum extract.
Add cake mix 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Chill, covered, for 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for several minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: easy cherry-fudge cake
directions: Combine cake mix, cherry filling, almond flavoring and eggs by hand.
(Note: Do not mix cake according to package directions.) Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.

title: seafood lasagna no. 1
directions: Bring 4 quarts water with a little oil in it to a boil and add salt.
Drop noodles one at a time into water.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes (should be only half-cooked).
Run noodles under ice water and set aside.
Chop flounder into 1/2-inch squares and mix with crabmeat, scallops and shrimp in a large bowl.
Melt the butter and saute the mushrooms for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain. Combine Bechamel Sauce, Ricotta and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese with eggs and mushrooms.
Put layer of noodles on bottom of buttered 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Put one-third of the fish mixture and one-third of the cheese mixture on top of the noodles.
Add one-third of the Mozzarella.
Top with noodles.
Repeat process twice more, ending with a layer of cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with the last of the Mozzarella and the parsley.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with remaining grated Parmesan at serving time. Serve 8 to 12.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat, add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and syrupy.
Remove from heat, add Rice Krispies cereal. Stir until well coated.

title: chicken devon
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package being careful not to overcook.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Layer broccoli in oblong dish that has been buttered.
Then add a layer of chicken and then sauce.
Repeat.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in water until barely tender.
Drain.
Cook onion gently in 1/4 cup butter until lightly brown.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add pepper, celery salt and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Place carrots in a shallow casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over carrots.
Top with bread cubes which have been mixed with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: my favorite pecan pie
directions: Cream butter;
add sugar and syrup, creaming constantly. Add the salt to the eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs to
the
first
mixture.
Add
the vanilla and broken nut meats. Pour into
a
9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apple-cinnamon pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
With mixer at low speed, alternately add flour and milk, ending with flour mixture.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Spread batter evenly into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken wings in a crock-pot
directions: Rinse chicken wing drummettes and pat dry. Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper and place on a broiler pan. Broil 4 to 5-inches away from the heat for 20 minutes, turning wings once during the middle of broiling. Transfer the wings to the crock-pot. Combine barbecue sauce, honey, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce in a mixing bowl. Pour over wings. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or on high for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Serve with Ranch or Bleu cheese dressing!

title: kids' favorite french toast
directions: Spread 6 slices of bread with peanut butter and 6 slices with jelly.
Put slices together to make peanut butter and jelly sandwiches.
Set aside.

title: buffet beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased casserole. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups in a bowl.

title: mrs. urie's plum pudding
directions: Mix all thoroughly, then add soda dissolved in the boiling water.
Add 2 cups sifted flour.
Steam 3 hours in greased mould, coffee cans or pint jars.
Serve steaming hot.
Any desired spices may be used.
Serve with hard sauce flavored with any desired flavoring.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding according to box using only 1/2 the amount of milk.
Mix in Cool Whip, then add Schnapps to taste.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cottage cheese tuna salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in vinegar and salt. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into an 8-inch ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on greens.
Garnish with more cottage cheese and radish roses. Serves 6.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for several hours. Shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: giant ginger cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and molasses. Add 1/2 flour, beat, add rest and stir. Form into 2-inch balls. Roll in sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover with buttered crumbs after placing in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn sticks *
directions: Combine all ingredients; add enough buttermilk for desired consistency.
Pour into hot, oiled cornstick pan.
Bake at 500° until brown.
Makes 7 cornsticks.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix milk with cream cheese. Add instant pudding.
Spread on cake.
Top with pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli together on one pan till done. Drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix broccoli and noodles with mushrooms and butter. Stir in the rest of the ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes or until thick.
(More milk can be added if it gets too thick.)

title: orange jello salad
directions: Thoroughly drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix package of Jell-O, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and drained pineapple and oranges.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Chill and enjoy!

title: crock pot lasagna
directions: 1. Brown hamburger, onion, and garlic in skillet.
Drain.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine egg, milk and bread; beat until bread is in fine pieces.
Stir in salt, pepper, nutmeg, minced onions and ground chuck.
In skillet, saute sliced onions until golden; set aside. Shape meat mixture into small meatballs and brown in oil.
Remove to 1-quart casserole.

title: soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Slice sausage real thin and brown lightly.
Cube potatoes.
Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cook for at least 3 hours.
Add seasonings.
Invite the family over for some soup.
They'll love it.

title: dirt
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese well, then add pudding mixes, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix together well.
Layer crushed cookies on bottom of pail; alternate cream cheese/Cool Whip mixture, worms and crushed cookies.
Top with crushed cookies and shovel or plastic flower in a pot.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Place apples in a saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender. Add butter, sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice; mash well. Divide pastry into 3 equal portions; roll out on waxed paper. Cut out pastry circle, using a 5 inch saucer as a measure. Place about 3 Tbsp. of apple mixture on half of each pastry circle. To seal, dip fingers in water and moisten edges of circles; fold in half, making sure edges are even. Using a fork dipped in flour, press pastry edges firmly together. Heat 1 inch of oil to 375°. Cook pies until golden brown on both sides, turning only once. Drain well on paper towels. Makes about 1 1/2 doz.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Add margarine and soup.
Do not add water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix well. Turn heat off and add rice.
Let set about 20 minutes.

title: cracker pie
directions: Continue beating egg whites until sugar is dissolved.
Fold in 3/4 cup cracker crumbs (saltines) with 1 teaspoon baking powder sprinkled over.
Add 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
(Watch carefully.)
Let cool.
Spread top with 1/2 pint whipped cream with sugar added. Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Chill.
Cake part can be baked in advance.
It is usually lower in the center when done.

title: coffee cake
directions: *Add 1 tablespoon vinegar to measuring cup and fill with milk to make 1 cup total.

title: scallop cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage; boil and drain well.
Layer cabbage, pepper, pimento, bacon and cheese.
Pour the white sauce over all and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy creamy mushroom garlic chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup and milk.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: beef in a bun
directions: Brown ground beef in pan; drain.

Add Manwich sauce; mix well. Place canned biscuits in a 12-count, lightly greased muffin pan. Mold biscuits in each holder as to look like a cup, then spoon in Manwich mix, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons to each cup. Bake in oven at 400°, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; eat while hot.

title: "yam bake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain yams, discard liquid and drain pineapple chunks (save liquid).
Mix all ingredients together. Place in Corning or Pyrex bowl.
Put marshmallows over top to brown, about 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pistachio pie
directions: Add whole can of drained pineapple to pistachio pudding crystals.
Let stand a short while.
Add 3/4 package of Cool Whip. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shell or crumb pie crust. Add remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle top with nuts or jimmies.
Put in refrigerator to jell.
Serve!

title: grape jelly
directions: Cook grapes until done.
Run grapes through colander.
Mix juice and sugar and cook until it starts to jell.
When it gels, it sticks to end of spoon and looks thick.
Then pour in jars and seal.

title: coconut crunch torte
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until peaks. Fold graham cracker mixture into egg whites.
Spread in well-greased 9-inch pie pan or 10 x 6 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut and serve with any flavor ice cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger; slice potatoes (thin) and slice onion.
Layer potatoes and onion.
Pour in drained hamburger.
Layer potatoes and onion.
Pour cream of mushroom on top.
Bake for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are done. Spray casserole dish with Pam!

title: teen swinging punch
directions: Mix juices in punch bowl.
Add coloring for desired effect. Slowly pour in club soda.
Yields 20 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom of a loaf pan.
Mix all the ingredients and beat for 30 seconds. Pour into the pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes. Cool slightly and remove from the pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: flamin' chicken
directions: Create	the
glue by finely dicing the first 7 ingredients. Saute
the	vegetables
in	2 tablespoons butter for 10 minutes. Turn down heat and stir in a little water, flour and Tabasco sauce
to
create
a
paste.
Simmer
for
a few more minutes and set aside.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: *May mix with ground pork, turkey or veal.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs and sugar. Put into a 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle breadcrumbs on top. Bake at 350° until brown and crusty on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover beans for the last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: date bars
directions: Cook brown sugar, dates and water until thick.

Mix together flour, oats, brown sugar, salt, baking powder and Crisco. Press firmly into bottom of square cake pan 1/2 of the oat mixture. Pour date mixture on top and cover with remainder of the oat mixture and pack down lightly.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: crunchy coconut delights
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine mashed potato flakes, sugar, oleo, milk and coconut extract; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
Stir in flour, coconut and nuts (dough will be stiff).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until firm to touch (cookies should not brown).
Remove from cookie sheets. Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar.
Return to rack to cool completely.
Makes 36 to 48 cookies.

title: kitty korn
directions: Pour 1/2 cup melted oleo into large baking pan.
Add popped corn and nuts.
Combine remaining oleo, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt in a large pot and boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over corn mixture.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes (STIRRING EVERY 15 MINUTES).
Makes about 7 quarts.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add sweet milk.
Roll nuts, dates and raisins in flour.
Add spices and baking powder with flour.
Chop apples and add last.
Bake in layer until done.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar and cream. Stir in syrup and 1/2 cup milk.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Pour into 1/2-gallon freezer container.
Stir in enough milk to fill container 3/4 full.
Add vanilla.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.
Yields 12 servings.

title: salmon croquettes for 2
directions: Combine well all ingredients.
Form into patties.
Roll in flour and fry in a skillet in about 1/4 inch of oil.
Turn to brown on both sides.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Cool.
Pour cooled oil mixture over grated cabbage and onion.
Sprinkle with celery seed. Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: party chicken
directions: Place chipped beef and bacon in casserole.
Lay chicken (salted) on top.
Cover with soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake slowly 3 hours at 275°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine three ingredients and mix well together.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Top with strawberry pie filling and chill. Press chopped walnuts into pie crust prior to baking them in the oven.

title: gravy type chicken moli
directions: Boil fryer until done.
Set aside, with broth.
In large skillet, stir about 1/2 cup peanut butter, add about 1 cup broth. Stir in chili powder to desired taste and color.
Add more broth until amount of gravy needed.
Add more peanut butter until desired consistency.
Add the fryer (deboned if desired), cover and simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over white or Spanish rice or over mashed potatoes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 2 cake pans and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Mix in bananas.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add alternately with sour milk to banana mixture.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Makes 1 loaf banana bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, broth and sour cream.
Melt the butter.
Crush crackers and mix crumbs in butter.
Spread 1/2 cracker mixture in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Over this, spread chicken pieces. Over this pour mixture of sour cream, broth and soup.
Top this with remainder of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. May be frozen before or after baking for later use.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray pans with cooking spray. Pour mixture in pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool pies completely and top with Cool Whip.
This recipe makes two pies.

title: banana fruit punch(blender)
directions: Boil the water and sugar for 3 minutes and cool.
Blend in blender the bananas, orange juice and lemonade.
Add and mix pineapple juice.
Mix together with sugar and water.
Freeze mixture in small (approximately 2 cup) plastic containers.
When ready to use, thaw 1 to 2 hours and mix 1 part base to 3 parts 7-Up.
Serves large crowd.

title: fresh fruit and dip
directions: Wash strawberries, grapes, apples or whatever type of fruit you like.
To make the dip, mix box of instant vanilla pudding and sour cream together on medium speed until creamy.
Then, just dip your fruit.
Children love it!

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let come to a boil, cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Makes about 28 cookies.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan.
Cover with water; cover pan and boil 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and peel.
Cut potatoes and beef into 3/4-inch dices.
In a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter in oil.
Saute onion 5 minutes.
Add pepper and seasonings; saute for 10 minutes.
Add beef and cook 5 minutes, flipping with spatula.
Top with parsley.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients and eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add strawberries and beat until they are pulverized and well mixed with other ingredients.
Bake in two layers at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Ice when cool with Strawberry Icing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
Add oil, pumpkin and eggs (beat eggs before adding to recipe).
Mix until batter is smooth.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased bread or muffin tins.
Bake bread for 1 hour at 350°.
Bake muffins at 350° until toothpick inserted into
muffin comes out clean (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: saltine squares
directions: Line a jelly roll sheet with aluminum foil.
Coat with butter or Pam.
Cover with a layer of saltines.
Melt and boil 3 minutes: sticks of oleo and brown sugar.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over all.
Wait a minute, then spread evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle finely chopped nuts on top.
Cool.
Put sheet in refrigerator to chill.
Cut or break apart.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: west virginia hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until thick, stirring often.
Serve on hot dogs or in a plain bun for a "chili sandwich."
Finely chopped onions and a little mustard add a tasty touch.

title: potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw.
Mix all ingredients and top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed gouda cheese
directions: With a sharp knife, cut 1/4-inch off the top of the cheese and remove the top circle of wax.
Scoop out inside cheese, leaving 1/4-inch on the bottom and sides.
Place scooped out cheese in a blender or food processor and add sherry.
Blend until light and fluffy.
Spoon cheese back into the Gouda shell and garnish with a sprinkling of paprika.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburg in skillet. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Let cool.
Cook vegetables according to directions; let cool.
Cook chicken breasts at 350° for 30 minutes.
In an 8 x 11-inch Pyrex bowl, mix mayo, buttermilk, cheese and basil.
Add pasta, chicken and vegetables; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Chill.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Mix butter and cheese well.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in Rice Krispies by hand.
Pinch off small ball portions (about size of walnuts).
Flatten out balls on cookie sheet with a fork. Bake at 360° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool; store in tight container.

title: christmas pickles(a family favorite)
directions: Drain pickles; discard the liquid.
Slice each pickle into lengthwise quarters or chunks.
Put pickles back in jar.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put lid on tight and let stand at room temperature, shaking jar several times during the day to help dissolve the sugar.
Refrigerate until they are used up.

title: breakfast sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and dates.
(Cut dates in half or buy chopped dates.)
When sugar is dissolved, cook slowly 10 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
When cool, roll into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken with ranch dressing
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with kraut.
Pour Ranch dressing over kraut.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: texas beef stew
directions: Brown
meat
in
butter
in
a	large
Dutch oven.
Add vegetables.
Mix
soup,
milk and sour cream together.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour or until
meat is tender.
Sprinkle cheese over top of stew after serving into a bowl.

title: hot frank potato salad
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Drain off all but 4 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Add vinegar and water; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crumbled bacon, potatoes and hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot through.
Trim with slices of eggs.

title: shirley's creole seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use like salt, when it's salty enough, it's seasoned.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries and juice. Put in fridge until it begins to thicken.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into two 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: peach shake
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients.
Cover and blend.
Serve in a tall glass.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Stir in sour cream mixture and egg.
Gradually add flour to yeast mixture, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Punch dough down and divide in half.
Roll each portion to a 12-inch circle on a floured surface.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll each wedge, jellyroll fashion, beginning at wide end.
Place on greased baking sheets, point side down.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine, saute chopped pepper until soft.
Add soups and chicken (chopped); stir well.
In large 2-quart or more casserole, spray with Pam, layer spaghetti, chicken mixture and cheese. Repeat in same order.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breast thin.
For each serving, place 1 slice ham and 1 slice Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Can use after meal for your teeth.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings.
Dip each chicken breast rolled in Butter Buds, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Arrange in baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Drizzle with remaining Butter Buds.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Scald sweet milk long enough to melt 1/3 cup shortening or butter.
Let cool.
Soften yeast in warm water.
In large mixing bowl combine 1/3 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons salt and eggs.
Beat with spoon.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and satiny, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: wedding soup
directions: Boil chicken legs and bouillon to form a rich broth in an 8-quart pot.
Remove chicken and clean and chop into small pieces. Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and pepper.
Form very tiny meatballs and brown in a skillet.
Drain grease.
Add meatballs and chopped chicken to broth.
Slice carrots very thin and chop the endive into small pieces.
Add both to the broth.
Boil the pasta in a separate pan until slightly under done (al dente).
Add pasta to broth.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Romano cheese.

title: diabetic old-fashioned rice pudding(calories: 238)
directions: Wash the rice and place in a large-size individual casserole. Pour 1/2 cup of milk over the rice and set dish in a pan.
Place in a moderate oven.
Allow to bake until a brown crust forms. With a spoon, turn the crust under and mix with the rice.
Do this two or three times during the baking.
As the milk is absorbed by the cooking of the rice, pour the remaining milk into the dish. During the last part of the cooking, add the vanilla and the cinnamon.
As soon as the rice is soft, remove from the oven and chill.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into pieces.
Put in skillet and saute in lard. When brown, remove and cool pieces.
Beat eggs.
Dip rabbit in egg and then into bread crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry until brown.
Remove rabbit from pan and slowly add flour and milk.
Stir until gravy thickens.
Pour over rabbit and serve.

title: chicken crescent
directions: Pick boiled chicken off bones in small pieces.
Unroll crescent rolls and place chicken on wide end of roll.
Fold sides to the middle.
Mix soup and milk with half of cheese.
Place rolls in dish and pour mixture over top.
(Optional to pour some soup in bottom of dish before laying down the rolls.)
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° to 400° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: black olive sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread on bread with crusts removed.
Cut into triangles.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cut your sweet potatoes up.
Place in layers in a pot.
Between every layer use a half cup sugar and then a half stick butter. Pour milk in last.
Let it cook slow over medium heat on top of stove until done.

title: uncle jim's slaw
directions: In blender or food processor, mix first 4 ingredients. Sprinkle mixture with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and let stand for 1 hour.
In saucepan, heat last 4 ingredients, then allow to cool. Pour over cabbage mixture and refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place on large shallow baking pan that has been greased. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: Clean oysters; steam with a little water until oysters curl up.
Add milk, canned milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste. Cook on medium heat until boiling.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Freeze.
Can be eaten frozen or at room temperature.

title: fruited flank steak
directions: Sprinkle flank steak with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Drain fruit cocktail, saving 1/4 cup syrup.
Combine 1/4 cup syrup with remaining ingredients.
Pour over steak in pot. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until tender.
Add drained fruit the last few minutes.
Lift out of pot.
Place on platter.
With sharp knife, cut thin slices of meat across the grain.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: bavarian supper soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine all ingredients. Cover and cook over medium-low heat until vegetables are thawed and mix boils (about 10 minutes). Simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: pao doce (portuguese sweet bread)(requires patience, but well worth it)
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Save 1/4 cup of the water they were boiled in.
Mash potatoes and measure 1 cup.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and yeast to lukewarm potato water.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in mashed potatoes and set aside until mixture doubles in size.
Scald milk; add salt and cool until lukewarm.
Set aside.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, then mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and stir together.

title: three-bean dish
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Mix beans and meat together.
Add remaining ingredients; put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan cook and stir okra, onions and green peppers in butter over low heat until onion is tender.
Stir in consomme, tomatoes and bay leaf.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken and parsley; heat through.
Serve in bowls with scoops of rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas pecan brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo and water in saucepan, stirring over low heat until sugar melts. Then turn heat higher and cook until it spins a 6 or 7 inch thread (238° on candy thermometer). Add peanuts and cook slowly until it turns golden brown. Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt and soda.
While it is still foaming, pour on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Add flour, cumin, chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic salt and mix.
Add tomato juice and stir.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Drain the cans of kidney beans and add them.
Cover and cook another 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
Peel and slice thinly.
Fry bacon slowly in skillet; drain on absorbent paper.
Crumble. Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes and crumbled bits of bacon carefully.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand until ready to serve.
(This is good served with corned beef.)

title: block party beans
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add onion and celery, cook until tender.
Add soup, paste and ketchup, simmer 15 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add sugar, salt, dry mustard and Cheddar cheese.
Toss with fork.
Pour in beer.
Mix together with fork until all dry ingredients are moist.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Put mix into pan and spread evenly into corners.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: erna martin's icebox cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together the flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Make into rolls.
Cover with wax paper. Refrigerate. Slice and bake when needed. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peppermint bark candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, syrup and salt.
Cook over medium-high heat until dissolved.
Cook to 234° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool 10 to 15 minutes without stirring at all.
Add vanilla.
Beat until glossiness goes and turns dull. Add candy.
Put in pan quickly.

title: party pink salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and marshmallows.
Place over low heat; add gelatin and stir until all are dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and pecans; fold in whipped cream.
Put in dish and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool.
Cook macaroni, onion and pepper in broth until tender.
Cut up chicken.
Leave macaroni in broth and add chicken.
Stir in soup.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer chicken and macaroni mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crisp pastel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, jello, egg and vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: yellow punch
directions: Boil sugar and 2 c. water together to mix thoroughly.
Dissolve jello in 4 c. hot water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add juices and extract.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables, crackers or chips.
Garnish as desired.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: olive crispies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together well.
Slice bread thin. Smear mixture over bread slices.
Top as desired with pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese, sausage, ham, etc.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until crisp.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Pour off about half of drippings.
Allow to cool. Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper to bacon grease.
Add vinegar and bring to a rolling boil until it crystallizes.
Mix potatoes and chopped onion.
Pour hot mixture over onion and potatoes.
This will cook the onions on top while you pour it on. Add pimento or parsley flakes for decoration, if desired.

title: asian beef noodles
directions: Stack beef steaks; cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
In medium bowl, combine beef, jalapeno pepper and oil; toss to coat.

title: a tasty dish(president reagan's favorite food)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni in water.
Drain and place in casserole.
Add sharp Cheddar cheese, cubed, salt and pepper.
Mix in ham, cut in chunks.
Cover with milk.
Sprinkle crumbled saltine crackers over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Makes six to eight servings.

title: tuna dill sandwich
directions: Stir together dressing, dill and pepper.
Add tuna, onions and carrots; mix thoroughly.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand for 30 minutes before using.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar and eggs (one at a time), beating well after
each
egg.
Add
extract
and
flour (sifted with baking powder).
Last,
add nuts and raisins to which some of the flour has
been sifted on top and coated the fruit.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Spray loaf pan with Pam or grease with margarine.
Combine all ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(You may wish to remove foil last 15 minutes of baking so that the salmon loaf browns lightly.)

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar well.
Add vanilla and eggs. Put one vanilla wafer in the bottom of cupcake papers and fill 3/4 full of the cream cheese mixture.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes. Let cool and top with your favorite pie filling.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias slice carrots 1/2-inch thick.
Boil carrots in salt water, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
In small pan, add sugar, ginger, cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add orange juice and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots.
Toss to coat. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Blend cake mix with melted butter. Reserve 1 c. for topping. Add egg to remainder of mix. Blend well. Press in 9x13 pan.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Spread the rhubarb in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the sugar over the rhubarb, then the Jell-O, followed by the dry cake mix.
Combine the cold water and lemon flavoring and carefully spoon over the cake mix layer.
Melt the butter or margarine and drizzle over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: tomato butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook very slowly until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: chicken and vegetables vermouth
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; set aside.
Combine cheese and pepper in a plastic bag; close bag securely and shake to mix. Add chicken to cheese mixture.
Close bag securely; shake well to coat chicken.
Place butter in an 8-inch square baking dish; microwave at High for 55 seconds, or until melted.
Remove chicken from plastic bag; place in baking dish.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at Medium-high (70% power) for 6 to 7 1/2 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender. Drain and place in greased casserole. Make a sauce of the butter, flour, milk, cheese, salt and pepper. Sprinkle broccoli with almonds, then pour on cheese sauce. Sprinkle top with crumbs and bacon. Place in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling and browned on top.

title: pot roast
directions: Place onion soup mix in bottom of the roaster.
On top of this, put the roast and pour in the mushroom soup and water.
Cook on top of stove to a good steam, then lower heat and cook slow for 2 hours.
Then remove top and add potatoes and carrots; simmer 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice and a green salad, to complete meal.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Scald milk with liquid from oysters.
Melt butter in the hot milk.
Add oysters.
Remove green stomach, if desired.
Crumble the crackers into the hot milk mixture, remembering to keep consistency juicy rather than dry.
Pepper to taste. Let stand a while before filling bird cavity.
Will make enough to fill bird and casserole.

title: french roll pizza
directions: Grate cheeses and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Makes 2 quarts.

title: sweet and sour dressing for wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and put aside.
In the same skillet, cook onion in 1/4 cup of the bacon grease.
When onion is tender, blend in flour, sugar and salt.
Add water and vinegar. Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour hot mixture over leaf lettuce or Swiss chard.
Garnish with the crumbled bacon slices.
Serve immediately.

title: pretzel mix
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in cheese and seasonings, then add other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool and serve.

title: cake icing
directions: Cook until it boils.
Let stand until it cools.
Put powdered sugar in until thick enough to spread.

title: caramel cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 of the milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add remaining milk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Add vanilla. Beat 1 minute.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until centers spring back when pressed lightly with fingertips.
Cool in pans on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: crow nest pickles
directions: Slice pickles thin.
Let these remain in this liquid.
Add 8 garlic buds to pickles.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pack in jars; cover and let stand a week or 10 days.
It's the sugar that makes the pickles crisp, so don't scrimp on the sugar.

title: easy mints
directions: Put cream into a large bowl and add the sifted sugar gradually.
Stir the mixture smooth.
Use more sugar if it is necessary to have a thicker paste.
Add flavoring.
Put into icebox to chill.
When making into mints, melt in a double boiler and add a few drops of cake coloring.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: strawberry pie and 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix in double boiler and cook, then beat 7 minutes.
Pour over cold sliced strawberries.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerated yeast rolls(makes 24 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat two minutes.
