Add egg, oil and rest of the flour. Mix until smooth.
Put a little oil on the top of the dough. Cover bowl and refrigerate for two hours.

title: hearty mushroom and beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add mushrooms and saute until golden.
Remove and set aside.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil and heat until hot.
Add 1/2 of the beef cubes. Brown well on all sides.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion and remaining beef cubes.
Saute until meat is brown and onions are golden.
Return all meat to pot.
Add broth, tomatoes, salt, oregano, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered until meat is almost tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots and simmer covered for 7 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into soup along with rice and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until soup is slightly thickened and mushrooms and rice are heated, about 20 minutes.
Stir in wine.
Heat 2 minutes longer.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar and flour.
Then add the melted margarine.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Hawaiian or egg bread.

title: orange juice pork chops in crock-pot
directions: Coat pork chops with paprika.
In a large skillet over medium heat, brown pork chops in oil.
Place chops in slow cooker. Combine orange juice, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour
over chops. Cover and turn heat control to low. Cook 6 to 8 hours or until done.

title: terrific muffins
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Mix in flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mash 1/2 cup fruit, then add along with other 2 cups of fruit.
Stir well. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on top of filled muffins.
Bake in large 12-muffin pan for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Jell in freezer quickly. Whip can of milk and add to jello.
Add vanilla while whipping; set aside.
Whip sugar and cream cheese together.
Whip with other mixture and put in graham cracker crust.

title: herbed tomato spread
directions: About 2 hours before serving:
Slice tomatoes and arrange in serving dish in overlapping slices.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
If desired, garnish with parsley.

title: sunshine pork loin roast
directions: Combine orange juice, honey, mustard, Tabasco sauce and nutmeg; set aside.
Rub roast with cooking oil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Insert rotisserie rod lengthwise through center of thermometer at an angle so tip is in center of roast but not touching rod.
Place roast on rotisserie of grill preheated to 325°.
Cook until juices form and rotate on roast, then brush glaze on roast with pastry brush every 10 minutes.
Cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate bits and butter in double boiler; add egg and cool.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Form into a roll; freeze. Slice.

title: spinach soup
directions: Boil spinach in water with chicken stock and potatoes until potatoes are soft.
Puree and return to saucepan.
Add cream and seasonings.
Saute onions until clear.
Add to soup.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Cake:
Mix and bake by package directions in sheet pan.

title: water chestnut roll-ups hors d'oeuvres
directions: Let chestnuts stand in soy sauce about 30 minutes (large chestnuts may be cut in half or thirds to make 18 chestnuts). Roll each in sugar, then wrap with strip of bacon. Secure with wooden pick.
Place in shallow baking pan or broiler pan.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or broil 4 to 5-inches from heat about 8 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Makes 18.

title: garlic chicken with grapes
directions: Mix together mustard, soy sauce, honey and vinegar; set aside. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix together garlic and oil.
Place chicken in pan, skin side down (skin optional).
Make sure chicken is covered by oil and garlic on both sides.

title: muslim bean soup
directions: Soak beans for several hours or overnight.
Wash and place in 3-quart pot.
Add vegetables and all remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to cover beans well.
Bring to boil and cook slowly until beans are completely soft and mashable.
Add more boiling water, if needed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 400° for 45 minutes.
This may be baked in a large ring mold and filled with beef stew, chili or chicken a la king.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Cook ribs with onions for about 45 minutes at 400°;
drain. Heat remaining ingredients, then add heated ingredients to ribs. Cook another 45 minutes, basting with sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and milk in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Test in cold water to see if it forms a soft ball, if not boil 3 minutes more.
Take from stove and add butter, vanilla, salt, oats and peanut butter.
Stir and drop by heaping spoonful on wax paper.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all wet ingredients first.
Then add Jiffy muffin mix. Blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out cleanly.

title: casino dressing(bluefish, clams, etc.)
directions: Saute bacon until almost done, then add onion and green pepper.
Cook until veggies are done.
Add garlic, paprika and thyme.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pull from fire and stir in butter.
Cool and serve as topping.

title: macaroni beef saute
directions: Put everything in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 20 minutes covered.
Take cover off for a few minutes if too much juice.

title: malgamation cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add milk and dry ingredients that have been sifted together and mix well. Add stiffly beaten egg whites and mix. Bake in 9-inch cake pans, making 6 to 8 real thin layers. Bake at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Brown in heavy skillet.
Remove to casserole dish.
Take the tomato soup and add to drippings in skillet.
Add enough water to make a thin gravy; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: crunchy birthday cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar, egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture. Fold in corn flakes, oats, coconut and nuts.
Roll in small balls and place about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dumplings(little)
directions: Mix egg, salt and milk.
Add flour until it is thick enough to drop.
These are good in soups.
Use a teaspoon, but heat it up in hot soup.
Use the front-third of the spoon and your dumplings will be small, but firm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook chicken broth and broccoli until tender.
Add mushroom soup and cheese until the cheese is melted.
Serve over baked potatoes.
Divide in half for small family or great frozen.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Heat the above ingredients together (don't boil). Pour into freezer container. Layer with ice and ice cream salt until freezer is full.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and Cool Whip.
Put in baked pie crust.
Let chill to set.

title: bool koki
directions: Combine all
but meat in a bowl and stir.
Add the meat; turn it until it is coated with the marinade.
Let it marinate 1 or more hours.
(It needs no more than an hour.)
Sear quickly on a barbecue.
Serve hot with rice, cucumbers in vinegar and a green salad.

title: rice stuffed peppers
directions: Core and seed peppers.
Boil in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Stir in rice that has been cooked just enough to thaw. Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add soup, 1/2 cup water, celery and seasonings to rice.
Spoon into peppers.
Place into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: dog food
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in the microwave (about 3 minutes).
Pour mixture over Crispix cereal in bowl and toss.
Let cool a few minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Grease and flour well a 2-piece ring pan.
Mix all ingredients; stir in apples and walnuts last.
Dough will be stiff.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan. Check for doneness with a broom straw or toothpick.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse in cool water and drain.
Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until mixed well in frying pan. Add sherry, milk, bouillon cubes and 1/3 cheese.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add chicken and mushrooms to the sauce along with the spaghetti noodles.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/3 cup cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until bubbly and serve.

title: german slaw
directions: Salt and pepper cabbage in a large, covered dish.
Boil cabbage for 2 minutes; drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, oil and celery seed.
Let stand 24 hours.
The longer it stands, the better it tastes.

title: large monster cookies
directions: Yields 60 large cookies; halve the recipe for 30 large cookies.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring margarine, evaporated milk and cocoa to a boil.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Cook over low heat to smooth consistency.
Serve over ice cream.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Great for a group.
Fast and easy.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread as directed on package; cool.
Combine crumbled cornbread with ingredients.
Mix well; chill.
Better on second day.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes. Refrigerate 24 hours. Add tomatoes just before serving. Keeps fresh in refrigerator for two weeks, but won't last that long when served.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake.

title: bean dish
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, tomato paste, brown sugar, mustard, celery and onion.
Cook 15 minutes. Add and drain all cans of green beans, butter beans and wax beans.
Add pork and beans, kidney beans and hot chili beans.
Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350° with bacon strips on top.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove cake from pan and let cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix 1/2 can creme of coconut, condensed milk and half the Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture into holes.
Mix 1/2 can creme of coconut with remaining half of Cool Whip.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with coconut.
This cake can be frozen.
The longer it stays frozen, the better it is.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl beat Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Add egg and beat well.

title: versatile pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Combine pasta with next 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Set aside.

title: monkey ball cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each individual biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll into a ball.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon.
Put balls into tube cake pan.
Mix melted butter and leftover sugar and cinnamon, then pour over balls. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool for about 5 minutes and then turn out on a dish or it will stick.

title: rigatoni-beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in melted fat.
Cut large onion and brown with meat. Place meat and onions in kettle and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Half hour before serving meat and vegetables, cook rigatoni and serve in a platter around the stew.

title: tuna roll
directions: Blend all ingredients except parsley.
Mix well.
Shape into a roll.
Roll tuna in parsley and wrap in plastic wrap (may be frozen).
If frozen, remove one hour before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Boil, cool and debone chicken.
Crush chips.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Place deboned chicken over chips.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Keep cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together, except nuts and parsley.
Form in ball and sprinkle with nuts and parsley.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 2 gallons. (Best if served slushy.)

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and heat just before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave 1 cup pecans separate.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; chill well.
Form in ball and roll in cup of pecans.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Combine first five ingredients.
Add milk and shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour 3/4 cup of hot water over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cut into squares.
Spoon hot fudge over top and serve with whipped cream.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until tender; drain.
Add white sauce.
Mix in creamed corn.
Simmer until thick.
Add more milk if it is too thick. Serve with bacon and cheese.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: In large bowl, mix the Cool Whip, confectioners sugar, melted butter and egg yolks. In a different bowl, tear up angel food cake in small pieces. Pour Cool Whip mixture over cake and sprinkle crushed Butterfinger candy bars over the mixture. Layer cake, Cool Whip mixture and Butterfinger candy bars until gone. Refrigerate. Better if made night before.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Sift flour and soda; add to mixture.
Mix in potato chips and nut meats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups. Mix together all ingredients.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy peach upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with margarine.
Arrange peach slices in bottom of pan until evenly covered.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
In a medium bowl, prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Spoon over peaches, covering peaches well.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes. The top should spring up when lightly touched in the middle.
Remove from oven and serve warm with whipped cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple in greased 9 x 13 cake pan. Dump in pie filling and spread. Dump in cake mix. Spread evenly. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix. Put butter over top. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes. Serve warm or cooled. Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken devonshire
directions: Bake chicken breasts with 1/2 slice bacon for 25 minutes or until done.

title: easiest-ever baked pollock fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In small bowl, mix bread crumbs, cheese, lemon juice and melted butter.
(Mixture will be pasty.) Set aside.
Coat a baking sheet with nonstick spray and add the fillets.
Blot the tops with paper towel, then spread with mayonnaise.
Take the crumb mixture and spread it evenly across the tops of the mayonnaise coated fillets.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Optional:
Reduce number of potatoes and add 1 can butter beans.

title: tomato beef stir-fry
directions: Cut meat in strips.
In a bowl stir together cornstarch, soy sauce, sherry and water.
Add meat to coat.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoon oil and let marinate 15 minutes.

title: dilly artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth. Add the rest of the ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: upside-down banana cake
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Blend 1/4 cup of margarine and brown sugar; spread in prepared pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Stir lemon juice into mashed bananas. Blend together the other 1/2 cup of margarine and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time, blending until smooth.
Stir in sifted flour mixture alternately with banana-lemon mixture, mixing until smooth after each addition.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Stir in butter, cheese and eggs and form into crust in buttered pie pan.
Brown meat and add sauce.
Put in spaghetti crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs to the point of adding the water.
After adding water, add onion, peppers, salsa, bouillon and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Cook as package directs. Meanwhile, brown 1 pound ground beef; season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain.
Add 1 can red beans (drained) and 1 can whole kernel corn (drained).
Stir to mix and simmer 5 minutes.
When rice is done, mix meat mixture and rice together. Break tortilla chips in bite-sized pieces to make 2 cups.
Gently fold in rice mixture.
Sprinkle top of casserole with one cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add cubed cheese, pepperoni, drained and sliced olives, celery and onions.
Mix with Italian dressing and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and spices and add butter.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when cool and serve.

title: quickie peach pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix together milk, flour and sugar. Pour into baking dish with butter and swirl to mix. Add peaches with juice. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, 1 tablespoon sugar and melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and allow to cool.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add other ingredients, except coconut and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Pour into an ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: brisket and potato pancakes
directions: Sprinkle paprika generously on both sides of the brisket. Brown for 30 minutes on each side at 450°.
Lower heat to 350° and add salt, pepper and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake 2 hours.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixer into freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Turn churn off.
Cover with thick towel and let set 1 hour.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: sally's special salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in quart jar and shake vigorously.
Store in refrigerator and shake well before serving.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat with onion soup mix and salt and pepper to taste.
Add taco mix and follow package directions.
Make large green salad and add cheese and crushed chips.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Top with meat mixture.
Toss well.
Serve with sour cream and salsa as desired.

title: tijuana pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except the cheese and chips.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer Doritos, meat mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: stuffing topped chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts; add diced celery to water just before chicken is done.
After chicken is done, cut into bite size pieces.
Add celery, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: slush drink
directions: Mix together and put into freezer.
When frozen, add 1 ice cream scoop of slush to glass and fill with Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Flake salmon and place half of it into a greased baking dish. Season with lemon juice.
Cover with half of bread crumbs and repeat in layers.
Pour white sauce on top and bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage with onions
directions: Cover and steam on very low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cheesecake that you don't have to bake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave (1 minute).
Set aside to cool.
In bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and butter until smooth. On low speed, blend in melted chocolate.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust; cover and chill until firm.
Serve and enjoy!

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in large frypan.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer.
Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place 10 halves over bottom of ungreased 9-inch baking dish.
Mix well 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg. Remove meat from heat, stir in cream mixture and spoon over biscuit layer.
Arrange reserved 10 biscuits on top of meat layer. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and heat until dissolved.
Add peanut butter and stir until blended well.
Put corn flakes into a mixing bowl and pour peanut butter mixture over corn flakes and stir.
Drop onto wax paper with spoon.

title: bananas foster
directions: Put butter, brown sugar and honey in a large skillet; stir until melted.
Lower flame.
Add bananas, cut side down.
Cook on high heat until liquid begins to boil.
Lower flame to medium. Add rum and liqueur; cook until the liquid becomes thicker.
Turn bananas over to cook for a couple of minutes on the other side. Spoon the syrup over the bananas and serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: dressing for fowl
directions: Grind the gizzards, liver and pork.
Wash and cook rice. Brown in about 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add a little water at a time.
Let simmer and mix with rice all the browned ingredients. Season with poultry seasonings, sage or any other seasonings you prefer.
This may be stuffed lightly in turkey or other fowl or browned in casserole.

title: chunky cream cheese spread
directions: Combine
cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon extract; beat at
medium
speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Chill
until
ready
to serve.
Yields about 1 cup. Spread on cookies, toast or hot banana-nut bread.

title: white velvety meltaway dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Blend together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract and salt.
Gradually add 1/4 cup milk and gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in heavy cream, whipped.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch pan; chill until firm.
Serve with fresh fruit. Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix with first ingredients, stir well and chill overnight. Add crumbled bacon on top before serving.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Thaw frozen shrimp. Cook green pepper, onions and garlic in oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients except parsley and shrimp. Cover and cook 20 minutes. Add shrimp. Cook another 5 to 10 minutes until shrimp are done and rice is tender. Stir occasionally. Add parsley at end of cooking period. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Place onions and sugar in large saucepan along with 1/4 cup of broth.
Saute for 5 to 10 minutes until onions begin to soften, stirring often.
Add remaining stock and other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes more or until onions are very soft.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomatoes, peppers and seasoning mix.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer part of tortilla chips.
Next, pour meat mixture.
Spread sour cream. Layer half of cheese; add layer of tortilla chips, then rest of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together thoroughly. Pour into a baking dish. Melt margarine and pour into center of mix. Drain peaches (just a little) and pour into the center of the margarine. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat together beets and juice.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Stir into beets, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix the egg, margarine and apples with the mixed dry ingredients.
Pour into crust and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
This has no top crust and looks like toasted coconut when done.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and cook in a heavy saucepan until it reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Spoon drop or pour onto wax paper lined pan.

title: onion-topped chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 9-inch square baking dish. Arrange potatoes around chicken.
Combine soup and sour cream; spread over chicken and potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle with onions; bake 10 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: collards(better after frost)
directions: Wash and strip heavy stems from collards.
Slice fatback meat; soak in cold water for 1 hour.
Pat meat dry.
Fry in heavy pot or frying pan until all grease is fried out.
Place grease and fatback in large pot.
Add small amount of water.
Add sugar.
Cut collards up.
Drop drippings wet in hot grease.
Stir; cover and cook for about 45 minutes, or until tender.
Add salt when almost done.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Place bread crumbs on wax paper. Dip cutlets into egg mixture and coat with the bread crumbs.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Bring to boil sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Drop in Ritz; boil for 20 minutes.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake until brown.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Stir in meal.
Add 2 tablespoons shortening.
Mix well.
Slightly beat egg and add milk.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Using a spatula, spread each frankfurter with batter until evenly coated.
Deep fry as many at one time that will float uncrowded.
Makes 20 to 22.

title: apple-orange cooler
directions: In blender container, combine applesauce and orange juice. Add ice cubes, cover and blend until ice is crushed and mixture is almost smooth.
Makes 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, Crisco, oleo and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. When storing, put a slice of bread on top; this will keep cookies soft.

title: monkey bread
directions: Let rise until double in size.
(Note:
Add some of the flour before the yeast mixture in order not to kill the yeast in a too hot mixture.)
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
With sharp knife, cut into squares, triangles or rectangles.
Turn these geometric shapes in melted butter or oleo before placing in angel food tube pan.
Build up with the shapes until pan is about 1/2 full. Sometimes I use two pans.

title: fried rice
directions: Rinse rice once.
Bring the rice and 2 cups water to boil. Stir and cover with lid.
Turn off heat; let set.
Brown ground beef.
Add onion; stir until tender.
Add carrots, celery and peppers.
Stir-fry until vegetables begin to be tender.
Do not overcook.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and Accent; stir until well blended.
Serve hot.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan pour milk; add grated potatoes, then onions, green pepper, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Beat in egg.
Dot with butter.
Press all down firmly.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and then add cold water.
If jello and sugar are hard to dissolve, use all hot water.
Add salt and other ingredients.
Pour into flat container and refrigerate overnight.

title: matt's peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water (soft ball stage). Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and salt. Beat well.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Let cool and cut into pieces.

title: cheese squares
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and flour with a pastry blender. Mix thoroughly.
Chill for about an hour.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Put filling on squares and fold each corner into center. Squeeze together and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for about 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and chocolate together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: double cheeseburger pizza rounds
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Separate dough into 8 biscuits.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet. With bottom of flat 2-inch diameter glass or with fingers, press out each biscuit to form 3 1/2-inch round with 1/4-inch rim around outside.
Combine egg yolk and water; beat well.
Brush over tops and sides of biscuits.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, onion and 1/2 of the vinegar. Beat.
Add oil gradually while beating.
Add remaining vinegar in small amounts.
Beat until thick.
Add celery seed.

title: coconut sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Add coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Serve in flowerpot.
Crush the Oreos.
Mix pudding mix and milk together; add remaining ingredients.
Put layer of crushed Oreos on bottom of flowerpot, then layer pudding mixture. Alternate, ending with crushed Oreos.
Put plastic flowers in, then put into freezer.
Take out 20 minutes before serving.

title: oven-fried fish fillets
directions: Coat fillets with mayonnaise. Combine breadcrumbs, parsley and paprika. Dredge coated fillets in breadcrumb mixture. Arrange fillets on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until fillets flake easily with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges. Yield: 4 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in large bowl. Store in airtight container. When ready to use, place 1 tsp. (or more, according to taste) in one cup of hot water.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
One cup of flour can be added, if needed.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa-banana bread
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, bananas, milk, eggs and vanilla in large bowl; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; stir in banana mixture just until moistened.
If desired, blend in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: praline-taffy-apple pie
directions: Prepare crust.
On lightly floured surface, roll out half of the pastry to form a 12-inch circle. Fit into 9-inch pie plate. Trim even with rim of pie plate.
For top crust, roll out remaining dough and set aside.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine Bisquick, corn meal and sugar; blend in eggs, milk and melted butter in order.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly together; heat.
Add wieners.
Simmer until wieners are thoroughly heated.

title: onion rings
directions: Prepare onions under water to prevent tearing.
Slice separately into rings.
Mix remaining ingredients (except oil). Beat until batter is smooth.
Heat oil.
Dip onion in batter.
Fry in oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mimi's lemon bars
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients; put into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Stir together first 10 ingredients in a large bowl just until combined. Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Pour chili sauce over meat loaf and bake 20 to 25 more minutes or until meat is no longer pink in center. Arrange cheese slices in a crisscross pattern on top of meat loaf. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: blueberry brunch cake(or blueberry crunch)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour in pineapple with juice.
Add the blueberries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour box of dry cake mix over the blueberries.
Melt the margarine and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle on the nuts and coconut and top with the remaining 1/4 cup of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. About midway through cooking time, cut slits in cake to allow juice to come to the top of the cake.
Cool at least 25 minutes before cutting.
Serve with either whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes or up to 2 hours.
Cover and refrigerate for longer storage.
Return to room temperature before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 12.
Contains 12 calories, 10% calories from fat, 2 g total fat, 0 g saturated fat, 0 mg cholesterol, .5 g protein, 3 g carbohydrates, 93 mg sodium and .6 g fiber.

title: baked beans
directions: Parboil beans with pinch of soda.
Let boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and put on fresh water; boil for 1/2 hour.
Put 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy frypan and melt.
Do not burn.
Add water and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
This will crystalize, but keep stirring until dissolved.
Put beans in casserole.
Add sugar mixture, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Put pieces of salt pork around edge and 1 whole apple and 1 whole onion in center.
Bake at 350°.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cukes and onions and let set for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Sprinkle over the chicken mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot tuna pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayo, lemon juice, mustard, sugar, basil and salt.
Stir in shells, tuna and vegetables.
Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread cubes in scalded milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Gradually add beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Fold in raisins.
Bake in Pyrex dish in a pan of a little water until firm (insert knife in center to see if firm) at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan brown the tomato paste in the cooking oil. When tomato paste begins to brown, add the chopped onion and minced garlic.
Continue to cook until onion is transparent.
Add water and mix well. Add brown sugar.
Add tomatoes and spices. Reduce heat and simmer for at least 1 hour.
The longer you simmer, the better it tastes.

title: meltaway fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly, still using low heat, until butter is melted. Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan and chill until firm.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Shake up and down in large Tupperware bowl.
Then add the ice water; swirl around in bowl until it thumps.
To brown, bake at 425° approximately 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch square pan with butter.
In a bowl, toss together the apples, 1 Tbsp. flour and 1 Tbsp sugar.
Combine mixture in the pan.
In a separate bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Sift and combine 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup flour.
Gradually cut in the butter, one piece at a time, to the sifted flour to create a crumbly mixture. Sprinkle these crumbs evenly over apple mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees until bubbly and golden brown, for approximately 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix and flour until well blended. Add water, oil and eggs.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: reeses peanut butter squares
directions: Combine together crumbs, oleo, peanut butter and sugar.
Work until smooth.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 slices bread,	cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside. Cut remaining bread
into	1-inch cubes.
Place 1/2 of unbuttered cubes in bottom of	8
x
x
2-inch baking dish. Combine chicken,
onion, green pepper, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spoon over bread cubes.
Spread mushrooms over chicken mixture
and sprinkle
remaining
unbuttered bread cubes over mushrooms. Combine
eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Cover and chill overnight or
at least a couple hours.
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle with buttered cubes.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 50 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top last 5 to 10 minutes of baking.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In small bowl, beat first 4 ingredients until creamy, then add chocolate chips.
In large bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spray miniature cupcake tins with nonstick spray (Pam) and line with miniature paper cups. Spray cups.
Fill halfway with chocolate batter.
Put a heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture into center.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 36.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Brown beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring to mix, until heated through.
Layer the meat mixture in a greased casserole.
Top with 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup of nuts.
Shape into ball.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll in remaining nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: yellow squash with cheese
directions: Trim off ends of squash and cut into thin rounds, about 6 cups.
Heat oil in large, heavy skillet.
Add squash, shaking skillet and redistributing squash rounds.
Add garlic, salt and pepper and cook over high heat about 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with oregano and toss to blend.
Remove garlic.

title: microwave creamy potato bake
directions: Combine potatoes and onion in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover and microwave for 16 to 18 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Combine milk and flour in 4-cup glass measure.
Stir until smooth.
Add butter and microwave 4 to 5 minutes on Full power until boiling. Stir in salt, pepper, parsley and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes. Stir.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on Full power for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead together with fingers, until mixture sticks together. Place on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and beat well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with a mixture of brown sugar and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple and measure liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 cup and add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan, cover and put in refrigerator until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla; spread over salad.
Sprinkle the pecans on top.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook 4 minutes in Pyrex dish.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix spices with flour and sift; add to creamed mixture.
Heat applesauce; add to batter. Dredge fruits and nuts in 3/4 cup flour and add fruits to batter and mix well.
Grease 4 large loaf pans; place waxed paper in bottom.
Divide batter in pans and bake at 325 degrees about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 large loaf cakes (2-lb) or 8 small gift-size cakes (1-lb.).

title: june's cake
directions: Add oil and oranges to cake mix and beat to mix by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each egg.
Pour into 3 round pans, well-greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare dressing and butter (melted) and enough broth to moisten.
Place 3/4 of dressing in baking dish.
Top with chicken. Mix soup, sour cream and 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour over dressing.
Top with rest of dressing.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Arrange clean, deveined shrimp in a shallow baking dish. Simmer butter, olive oil, lemon juice, scallions and garlic for 2 minutes.
Pour liquid over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with linguine or rice.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make meat into patties.
Cut potatoes in slices, carrots into sticks, onion in slices and bell pepper in rings.
Stack on foil with onion and pepper on top.
Wrap up in the foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, or until carrots and potatoes are done.
Serves 5.

title: tofu icing
directions: Blend
until smooth and creamy.
Ice cake and refrigerate. Makes approximately 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: In a large dutch oven mix peppers, vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil. Boil for 10 minutes, remove from heat and add certo. Add a few drops of food coloring to color mixture. Pour into clean jelly jars. Boil lids and rings, clean jar lip and place lid and ring. Cover with a towel and let cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Beat until fluffy. Add one egg at a time with flour until all eggs are used.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: individual ham loaves
directions: Mix the ingredients and form into small loaves about 1/3 cup in size.
Cover with the following sauce and baste occasionally.

title: fresh coconut sheet cake
directions: Make up cake mix by package directions with the addition of 1 teaspoon of coconut flavoring and with all but 2/3 cup of the coconut.
(Reserve the 2/3 cup.)
Bake in a greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 x 3-inches deep by package directions.

title: meringue
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to beaten egg whites.
Beat again until stiff.
Put over mixture and brown in oven at 325° until golden brown.

title: tart cherry salad
directions: Drain
fruits,
reserving
juices.
Add
enough water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups and add sugar.
Bring to boil, stir in jello. Add
fruit
and
ginger
ale.
Chill until set, but not firm. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream
oil,
sugar
and
eggs.	Add
as
much flour and spices,
sifted together, as you can.
Add vanilla, apples and rest of flour;
mix well and add walnuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Cool to lukewarm temperature.
Whisk in one egg yolk at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Beat heavy cream until stiff.
Fold heavy cream into chocolate mixture. Refrigerate 5 to 6 hours minimum.
Decorate with shaved chocolate and raspberries.

title: pecan joys
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Blend in the following one at a time, powdered sugar, coconut and pecans.
(You may have to use your hands).
Shape into small balls.
Place on wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Put in freezer for about 5 minutes.
Balls need to be firm.
Dip in melted chocolate almond bark.
Place on a new sheet of wax paper to harden.
Hardens in seconds.

title: egg cheese(egg ost)
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Beat eggs slightly; add salt, sour cream and sugar and mix well together.
Add it, all at one time, to the boiling milk.
Let all this come to a slow boil until the whey comes, or until the cheese has separated from the whey. Remove from heat and remove the cheese to a dish.
Drain the cheese by placing it in a colander to drain.
After it is cooled, serve in individual dishes with sugar and cinnamon on top.
Serve on lefse, homemade bread or rolls.

title: skor candy
directions: Melt butter and sugar together over medium heat, bringing to boil.
Boil to taffy stage (crackles when dripped into water). Pour over crackers which have been placed on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian sandwiches
directions: Cut rolls in half and lay bottoms in pan.
Lay ham and cheese.
Spread 1/2 of glaze on top of cheese.
Put tops on and then spread rest of glaze.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Take all the fat off of the chicken. Place one piece of chicken in bread crumbs and then in the eggs and back into the bread crumbs.
Repeat with each chicken.
Fry chicken in the frying pan and let oil soak out from the chicken in a large baking pan.
Put some spaghetti sauce over the chicken.
Add some cheese to the top of the sauce.
Add more sauce over the cheese and then more cheese over that.
Bake for twenty minutes, until cheese is melted.
Let cool.
It's ready to serve.

title: * surprize packages *
directions: Wrap servings in foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very little clean-up!

title: mexican beef 'n macaroni
directions: Microwave beef, onion and pepper 5 to 8 minutes, until beef is done; drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, cumin and pepper.
Cover; microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Add topping.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cube bread; put in greased casserole.
Mix other ingredients; add to bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: *strawberry angel delight
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in oleo.
Add nuts.
Press into a 9-inch spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Gradually add lemon juice to Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended. Stir in strawberries.
Fold in whipped cream (or whipped Dream Whip, if used).
Pour over crumb crust and freeze.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: health cereal
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Put corn oil and honey over dry ingredients, stirring to mix well.
Spread in a cooking pan and brown coconut in oven.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Mix and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nanette's malasadas (fast portuguese doughnuts)
directions: Cut crusts off 8 slices of bread and cut them in quarters. Mix rest of ingredients together.
Dip each piece of bread into the batter, using a two-tined fork.
Deep-fat fry until browned. Drain them thoroughly and roll them in granulated sugar.

title: recipe for cowboy coffee
directions: Bring water to rolling boil.
Add coffee.
Boil for 2 hours. Throw in horseshoe (if it sinks, it ain't ready).

title: crunchy topped fish with potato sticks
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels; set aside.
Line a large baking sheet with foil.
Spray foil with nonstick spray coating.
Arrange potato sticks in a single layer over half of the baking sheet.
Brush potatoes with oil or the 2 teaspoons melted margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil
the first 8 ingredients together.
When cold, add the flour,
baking
soda,
salt and nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or more.

title: deep fried fish
directions: Cut fish into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Mix salt and corn meal mix in plastic bag.
Dip fish in milk.
Put fish in bag of corn meal mix.
Close bag and shake to coat the fish.
Heat oil in deep fryer.
Drop fish strips into hot oil and brown on both sides.

title: fantastic layered dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine.
Mix with flour and 1 cup nuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soft cookies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking soda with knife; cut butter in mixture.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Beat eggs and add.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: raisin bran muffins(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Place Raisin Bran and buttermilk in a large mixing bowl.

Let stand until flakes are softened. Add eggs, oil or margarine and sugar. Sift dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt) and add to first mixture. Add chopped nuts, if desired. Mix well. Batter may then be stored in airtight container in refrigerator for up to six weeks.
To bake, place in paper-lined muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers, onions and cilantro.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend until desired consistency.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 24 wooden sticks.

title: pear-lime jello mold
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Beat cream cheese with milk.
Slowly add to Jell-O and beat until fluffy. Chill until partially set.
Add fruit and pour into mold.
Serves 6.

title: easy microwave chocolate fudge
directions: In large glass bowl, combine chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk; stir together.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm about 2 hours.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds fudge.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice and dissolve gelatin.
Allow to cool.
Add coke, cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Chip cream cheese into mixture.
Stir, allowing cheese to remain in pieces.
Chill until firm.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the barbecue sauce.
Spread mixture evenly in loaf dish, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Spread the barbecue sauce over the meat mixture.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 12 minutes; rotate the loaf dish 1/2 turn. Microwave until center is no longer pink, 13 to 16 minutes longer. Remove to serving platter.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Top with additional barbecue sauce if desired.

title: mom's marinated steak
directions: Pierce meat with fork and sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Place in glass baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over meat and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Grill or bake until desired doneness.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Beat eggs well; then add next 8 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until well blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and remove from pan.
Good as is but better frosted with a cream cheese frosting.

title: home fries with onion
directions: Combine all ingredients; season with salt and pepper.
Cook in large skillet, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Remove the cover to brown potatoes.
Turn until brown.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer, beating until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; stir in okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into a deep skillet; heat to 350°.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into oil and cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt (if desired) and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Peel stems of broccoli and use as well as florets.

title: chicken flautas
directions: In 3 layers of foil, put salt and peppered chicken breasts, wrap and bake in an oven at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes (until done).
Cut up chicken and put in a frying pan with cumin and picante sauce.
On low heat, heat mixture thoroughly.
Put oil in a small separate frying pan.
Fry corn tortillas until soft (do not fry them stiff).
Drain on paper towels.
Take one tortilla, put in chicken.
Mix cheese and roll up.
Secure with toothpick. Lay on cookie sheet.
Repeat until chicken mix is gone.
Put cookie sheet in oven at 350° and heat until cheese is melted and tortillas are crisp.
Serve with sour cream and guacamole.

title: molasses fruit cake stack
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, blending well.
Add molasses and mix well. Alternate adding flour mixture and buttermilk until well mixed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked chicken pieces, onion, green onion tops, salt, celery and mayonnaise. Spread mixture over stuffing mixture (already in casserole dish).
Then spread remaining stuffing mixture over chicken mixture.
Mix eggs with milk.
Pour this over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: In large iron skillet, on low heat, add oil, onion, pepper and celery.
Fry gently until onion turns.
Add tomatoes and blend in other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes.
Continue to simmer to thicken or use 1 teaspoon flour and water.

title: maple peanut softies
directions: Put peanut butter in a medium bowl. Add maple syrup. Stir until mixed. Add dry milk powder. Stir well. Spread the mixture into a loaf pan. Pat it down to make an even layer. Sprinkle peanuts over mixture. Press them firmly. Chill for 1 hour. Cut into squares. Keep them covered and refrigerated when you are not serving them.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients: chicken, onion, chicken broth, eggs, mayonnaise and crackers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until brown.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Add peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix and drop by spoon. Allow to cool.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in a double boiler. Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating with electric mixer, until it stands in peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Continue to beat until thick enough to spread.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in the normal way (wash skins well); cut each one completely in half lengthwise and scoop out clean.
Brush remaining shells with melted butter inside and out.
Sprinkle with salt and place on oven racks.
Bake at 350° until crisp and brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
For more flavor, add cheese and bits.
Cook 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Dip palms of hands in powder sugar.
Shape chilled mixture into 1-inch balls.
Rechill, if mixture becomes too soft. Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well by hand.
Drop by tablespoons into large skillet with 1 inch of hot oil in it. Cook for a few seconds, then lift up with spatula so they do not stick to skillet.
They will then float.
Cook approximately 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain well.
Serve warm.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: *All these can be adjusted for taste.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: You can add other optional ingredients (onions, green peppers, etc.).

title: meatballs extraordinaire
directions: Blend together meat, egg, onion and salt.
Form into small meatballs, about the size of jack balls (100).
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Pour over meatballs and simmer in an electric skillet or regular frying pan over low flame for one hour.

title: beau monde dip(in round bread)
directions: Process chipped beef until finely chopped.
Combine with all other ingredients (except the bread) and mix well.
Hollow out the loaf of bread by cutting off the top and pulling out dipping size pieces and placing them on a serving platter around the outside of the bread.
Cut the top like you would cut a jack-o-lantern at an angle so that you can replace the top and it won't fall in.
Rub butter or margarine on the inside of the bread before you fill it so the dip will not seep through.
Fill it up with the dip and dig in!

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and butter until almost done.
Add vanilla and marshmallow.
Beat with beaters.
Pour on buttered plate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth with mixer. Refrigerate before serving.
Cut up fresh fruit (bananas, apples, strawberries, grapes, etc.).
Dip fruit and eat.
Yum-yum. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mountain oysters
directions: Scald the balls and skin.
Slice thinly and soak in cold water for 2 hours.
Drain; salt and pepper slices.
Flour lightly.
Heat oil, butter or drippings in a frypan.
Saute the slices, browning both sides.
Allow 1/4 pound per person.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Wash and scrub cucumbers carefully; cut into 1-inch chunks. Dissolve salt in water; pour over cucumbers.
Cover and let stand for 5 hours.

title: sweet dough
directions: Combine
oleo
and
milk
in saucepan.
Mix yeast, warm water and
the
2 teaspoons sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs
in cup
with
fork
and
add
to oleo and milk mixture. Combine
this with
the
yeast mixture.
Now add the half cup sugar
and
salt. Gradually
add
in sifted flour until right consistency.
Usually about 8 1/2 cups of flour is sufficient. It may
appear
a little thick but the recipe is a proven one. Let
the
mixture
set
for about 15 minutes.
Mix well again until
the mixture is smooth. Let rise about 50 minutes or so depending
on
warmth
in room. After dough has risen, divide into
egg size portions with a spoon and form balls.
Place on an
oiled
baking
sheet
about
an inch apart and brush with melted butter.
Let rise until light, then make indentation in each ball of
dough for fruit.
Sprinkle with Posipka Topping. Fruits most generally used are cooked, sweetened pureed prunes or apricots
usually
spiced
mildly
with cinnamon or nutmeg. Use of spices,
optional.
Cottage
cheese is also popular for filling.
It is blended
with a dash of salt, a hint of sugar, a bit of
lemon
juice
and
grated
rind.
Over fruit filling sprinkle the
crumb
mixture,
Posipka.
Let the kolaches rise again and when
the dough is light to the touch (approximately 20 minutes), bake
in
hot
oven for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and
again
butter each kolache before removing from pan onto a wire cooking rack or large board.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half of cake mix in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. In a double boiler, melt caramels with butter and milk.
Pour caramels over partly cooked cake.
Put chocolate chips and pecans over caramels.
Pour remainder of cake mix on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In 2-quart pan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until blended well.
Gradually add half and half.
Cook until mix is thick and smooth.
Stir constantly.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until well blended.
Serve as a hot topping or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: chili pie
directions: Place 2 cups Fritos in baking dish. Arrange onion and half of grated cheese on corn chips. Pour chili over onion and cheese. Top with remaining corn chips and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Can use 2/3 cup cocoa and 1 tablespoon shortening.

title: spam-macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions, drain fat.
Combine meat and cooked noodles.
Add cheese, soup, chili, water, peppers and beans.
Put in 2 9 x 13 pans.
Combine bread cubes, butter sprinkle over casseroles.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes this freezes real well.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add shrimp to hot macaroni.
Cool. Add other ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving.

title: apple cake dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix apples and sugar.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: greek style macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Cool pasta. Add Feta cheese, olives and desired amount of salad dressing. Toss and chill before serving.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses thoroughly.
Measure flour.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend in. Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes six dozen cookies.

title: pound cake with strawberry-banana topping
directions: Melt butter in a skillet on grill. Add sugar, lemon juice and rum flavoring.
Stir well.
Cook until sugar dissolves (2 to 3 minutes), stirring constantly. Add bananas and strawberries.
Cook until bananas are soft but not mushy (about 2 minutes).
Serve over pound cake or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost while warm with confectioners sugar icing.

title: korean salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together salad ingredients along with the crumbled bacon.
Add the dressing and toss again.
Serve immediately.
(Do not add the dressing until you are ready to serve the salad as it will slightly wilt the spinach and immediately start to lose its heat.)

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix well and sift once the first 4 ingredients.
Add the Crisco.
Dissolve the baking soda and vinegar; mix with the hot water and salt.
Add to mix.
Beat the eggs and vanilla and add to mix.
Beat at medium for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: veggie lasagna
directions: Use deep casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 lasagna noodles, vegetables, cheese, and bread crumbs.
Repeat layer.
Topping with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.	Bake for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: california pot roast
directions: Cut bacon into bite size pieces; fry until done.
Drain excess grease.

Add cubed zucchini to bacon; cook until zucchini is done. You may have to add a tablespoon of water with the zucchini. After zucchini is done, add the jar of mushrooms, the mushroom soup and enough water to make a sauce consistency.
Cook rice according to directions on the package.
To serve, pour sauce mixture over rice.
This is so delicious.

title: blackberry crisp
directions: In medium bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat to soft boil stage. Put cover on pan for first few minutes and cooking time will be shortened.
Remove from heat; drop in 2 tablespoons of butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Cool to 110° without stirring.
Stir; beat until it becomes thick and begins to lose its glossy look.
Pour immediately onto a buttered plate.
Do not spread.
Cut when set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine and let cool.
Cream eggs in butter and sugar.
Beat together.
Add the grated zucchini.
Add all dry ingredients.
Add raisins and chopped nuts (optional).
Sprinkle top with sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (less time for smaller pans).
Vanilla or lemon extract can be used instead of nuts and raisins.

title: broccoli puff(no salt)
directions: Mix mushroom soup, egg, milk and mayonnaise together.
Put broccoli in deep dish, pour mixture over.
Add cheese.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs; pour over cheese.
Bake 3/4 hour in 350° oven.

title: fruit dip(delicious)
directions: Melt Milky Ways with sour cream.
(You can melt in microwave oven on Medium for 2 to 4 minutes; stir often.)

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar, shortening, lemon rind and salt.
Beat in egg and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Serve as a salad or as a vegetable.
This is very pretty served in grapefruit cups.
Add the tomato and mayonnaise just before serving if convenient.

title: greek chili
directions: Cook hamburger, eggplant, onions, pepper and juice until done and tender.
Add tomato paste, broth and rest of ingredients.
Add 3 cups water; cook until ready to eat.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine cooked carrots, soup and cheese together in baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes.

title: clam supreme
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Add water to clam liquid to make 1 cup.
In saucepan, combine liquid, margarine, poultry seasoning and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Add flour; cook until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in clams.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put into casserole and sprinkle with cheese then potato chips.
Bake in 425° oven until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs well; add flour and beat well.
Add nuts, vanilla and apples.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: graham wafer dessert
directions: Crush graham wafers in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Press 1/2 crumbs into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cream sugar and butter and add eggs, one at a time.
Spread over crumbs.
Fold well drained pineapple into whipping cream (or Dream Whip).
Spread over first layer and cover with remaining crumbs.
Cover pan with foil and chill overnight in fridge.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken and onions. Pour remaining ingredients over chicken and let simmer 1 hour.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Top each cracker or toast round with 1 T of crab mixture.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
36 crackers.

title: crunch bar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Layer saltines on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch pan.
Boil butter and sugar 3 minutes.
Pour or spoon butter-sugar mixture over saltines.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes. Watch carefully.
Remove from oven and spread the chocolate morsels over the top of the cooked saltines (using the back of a spoon helps).
Don't let it cool at all before spreading the chocolate.
Cool in refrigerator.
Break into pieces and freeze.

title: buttermilk coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add flour, oil, sugar, buttermilk, flavoring and coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes in tube pan. Ovens may vary.

title: fruity iced tea
directions: Brew tea in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and cool.
Stir in grape juice and sliced fruit.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add eggs, vanilla, nutmeg, whole milk and condensed milk.
Mix together.
Strain mixture into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Pie will be shaky.
Overcooking will make pie water.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a 4 to 5-quart pan.
Bring to a full boil and allow to boil 5 minutes.
Place candy bars (broken into pieces), chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme and pecans in a large mixing bowl.
Add hot syrup.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: tennessee cabbage
directions: Lightly brown butter in an 8-inch skillet.
Add cabbage and stir well.
Cover skillet tightly and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir and cook another 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and cream or evaporated milk.
Cover.
Simmer 4 more minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serves 5.

title: coffee-can ice cream
directions: Wash out the cans.
In the smaller can mix the whipping cream, half and half, sugar and vanilla.
Cover with lid and place in center of larger can. Pack a layer of crushed ice around smaller can.
Sprinkle ice liberally with salt and alternately add layers of ice and salt to fill larger can.
Cover with lid.
Choose a hard, level surface, like a table, driveway, patio or cement walk and roll the can back and forth for 10 minutes.
Use a spatula to scrape ice cream from can sides to center.
Discard melted ice. Put smaller can back in larger can and add more ice and salt. Roll for 5 more minutes.
Taste.
You may add 1/3 cup raisins, diced peaches or strawberries, if desired.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and serve on crackers of your choice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudgy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: potato patties
directions: Using leftover mashed potatoes, mix potatoes and other ingredients.
Form into patties.
Fry in heated oil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chinese salad(sugar-free)
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin.
Add soy sauce and lemon juice.
Stir until ice is melted and gelatin is slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into bowl or individual dishes.
Chill until set and serve.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan on top of the stove.
Just make sure the mixture does not burn; stir often until melted.
(You can use the microwave to melt, but I prefer the stove top.)
Take from the stove.
Add the white sugar; beat well (I just beat by hand).
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add the vanilla, salt and flour; stir well.
Add the nuts.
Mix well; the mixture will be thick.
Spread it out into a 12 x 9 x 2-inch aluminum pan or 2 small oblong pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
The secret to a great brownie is to have a fudgy taste, not a cake texture.

title: planters' punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ice and enjoy!

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice/vermicelli.
Mix with ground beef and egg.
Shape into twenty 1 1/4-inch meat balls.
In a large skillet, brown meat balls; drain.
Combine contents of seasoning packet and water; pour over meat balls.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham and spinach.
Flatten into rectangle.
Spread ham and spinach on meat and then roll up.
Bake loaf at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add vinegar, oil and juice from beets.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer over low heat about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Steam broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain and coarsely chop.
Coat a 9-inch pie or quiche pan with vegetable spray.
In dish, layer broccoli, cheese and onion.
In a blender, combine milk, Egg Beaters, biscuit mix and seasonings.
Process for 15 seconds; pour over vegetables.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6.
Contains 218 calories and 9.5 grams of fat.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all together well; shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Chill well before serving.

title: brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place meat in heavy plastic bag and pour marinade over it.
Squeeze out air and fasten bag.
Marinade overnight or several hours.
Drain meat and place in roaster. Pour marinade over meat.
Cook 2 to 3 hours at 325°.
Baste often. Thicken marinade with cornstarch and use as gravy.

title: grandma's pudding cake
directions: Cream
the sugar with softened margarine.
Add eggs and beat together.
Add flour alternating with milk. Add vanilla. Pour into an 8-inch iron skillet (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back.

title: patsy's crock-pot hamburger casserole
directions: Place a layer of vegetables in the order given.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top.
Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour into crock-pot.
Cover and cook in the crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: orange salad(note:  this is the recipe we use for banquets.)
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Add jello and cold water; mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
Let congeal partly.
Add whipped evaporated milk and grated cheese. Pour in bowl.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat 5 cups of milk with cinnamon stick in double boiler. Beat egg yolks while adding sugar.
Add 1 cup cold milk and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Stir frequently with wooden spoon while cooking until it thickens enough to coat a spoon.
Remove from heat and chill for several hours.
Flavor with vanilla and serve plain
or with whipped cream or grated coconut.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine all seasonings with salad oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir gently halfway through baking.
Spread on paper towels.

title: baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
If fillets are large, cut into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix juice with onion and butter.
Dip fish in mixture.
Place in greased square pan.
Pour remaining mixture over fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: asparagus parmigiano
directions: Drain cooked asparagus and arrange in a shallow baking dish. Saute onion and garlic in oil until golden.
Add salt, hot pepper sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add thyme and tomato sauce; simmer 20 minutes longer.
Pour sauce over asparagus.
Place slices of Mozzarella cheese over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, salt, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add
flour
and
soda to creamed mixture.
Form into balls;
place
onto an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake
at
for	6
to 7 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Mix mustard and grape jelly in 1-quart (946 mi) boiler.
Slice each wiener in 5 cross sections and combine with mustard and jelly.
Cook on medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish. Yields 50 bite-size wieners.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix
meat,
rice,
onion
and seasoning together.
Form into small
balls.
Fry	in hot oil, turning frequently, until light brown,
but not crusty on the outside.
Add tomato sauce and water; cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In large pot blend flour, butter, milk,
(roux) let thicken. Bake potatoes, peel and mash (chunky). Add potatoes to roux add chopped onions, bacon crumbs, & cheese. Top with onion, cheese and sour cream.

title: special brownies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fat-free cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and make into two rolls.
Roll each in chili powder. Wrap in waxed paper and chill. Serve with fat-free crackers.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir over low heat until chocolate and shortening are melted.
Bring rapidly to a boil until mixture reaches 220° or for exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat gently until mixture is lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until icing loses its gloss, and is of a spreading consistency.

title: honey dill dressing
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, honey, lemon juice and dill seed.
Whisk to combine ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, whisk dressing.
Makes 1 cup.

title: corn and sour cream
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Blend in flour and salt. Gradually add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Add corn to sour cream mixture; heat thoroughly.
Fold in 1/2 of crumbled bacon. Place in serving dish.
Top with parsley and remaining bacon. Serves 4 to 6.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: In a large pot, combine first 6 ingredients.
Add onion and garlic that have been sauteed.
Simmer 1/2 hour, then add regular size or cocktail meatballs.
Simmer another 1/2 hour.

title: mexican breakfast eggs
directions: Brown the sausage.
Add the onion, garlic, green pepper, cumin seed and Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Make indentations in 4 spots and add the eggs.
Cover until poached.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and cover to let cheese melt.
Serve with biscuits.

title: apricot fizz
directions: Chill apricot nectar and ginger ale well.
When ready to serve, combine the nectar and ginger ale.
Dip rims of glasses into lemon juice, then into sugar.
Pour in Apricot Fizz and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add chopped mushroom stems. Cook until soft.
Add bread crumbs; your stuffing is done.
Clean out mushroom caps with a tiny spoon.
Fill with stuffing. Sprinkle caps with salt.
Bake in pan adding 2 tablespoons water to pan.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes.

title: my dad's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, water, butter and onion until onion is tender. Put in hamburger and cheese. Cook until potatoes are done on medium heat.

title: eva's cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Gradually add flour, mixing to make a soft dough.
