Shape into smooth rounds and chill for an hour. Combine dates, sugar and water in saucepan (can add chopped nuts, if you want to).
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until soft (about 5 minutes).
Cool.
Roll chilled dough (take out of refrigerator a little at a time) on floured surface.
Cut into a small round.
Place a teaspoon of date mixture on half of rounds. Fold and seal edges with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown.
May freeze.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Mix ingredients and heat well.
Serve with favorite crackers and sliced cheese.
Great and quick for a cold winter day!

title: blackberry-apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thick and fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine blackberries and apple slices; place in pie shell.
Combine sugar, tapioca and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Sprinkle over blackberries; dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough to 1/8-inch thick; place over filling.
Trim pastry, seal and flute edges.
Cut slits for steam to release.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potatoes.
Mix in potatoes. Put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered or greased pan.
Top with 1 cup corn flakes or 1 cup crumbled potato chips and 1/2 stick margarine (melted).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flavoring and flour. Beat until well blended and smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Turn oven down to 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix cereal, Fritos, pretzels and nuts.
Mix margarine, oil and spices; pour over dry mixture.
Bake at 200° for 4 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: hickory grilled pork roast
directions: Rub roast with olive oil and sprinkle with sea salt.
Combine rosemary, thyme and pepper.
Rub over roast and let stand 30 minutes.
Soak hickory chips in water for 1 hour.
Prepare charcoal fire, let burn 20 minutes.
Place hickory on coals.
Place roast on rack.
Cook, covered with grill lid, over medium-high coals (350° to 400°) 40 minutes, turning often.
Let stand 15 minutes before thinly slicing.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, chilies, onion, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups cheese (mixed); set aside 3 cups mixture and add chicken to remaining mixture.
Put 3 tablespoons mixture in each tortilla and roll up. Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan; pour remaining mixture over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese, green onions and paprika on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or until heated through.

title: cream cheese and chipped beef
directions: Cream the cream cheese, lemon juice and Lea & Perrins together well.
Add dried beef that has been chopped well.
Use enough mayonnaise to make right consistency for spreading.
Let sit awhile to allow flavors to blend.
Taste and add more Lea & Perrins and/or lemon juice, if necessary.
Spread on any variety of thin bread and cut for party sandwiches.
If stored in refrigerator, let soften before preparing sandwiches.

title: frosty fruit medley
directions: In a large bowl, combine the undrained pineapple chunks, walnut halves, orange juice and ginger.
Stir to mix well.
Add the strawberry halves, blueberries and coconut.
Toss gently to coat the fruit with juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Mix together sour cream, chicken soup and dry onion soup. Layer 1 package of defrosted broccoli, a layer of chicken and one-half of the soup mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Repeat once more, beginning with broccoli.
Sprinkle crushed onion rings over top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
(If the casserole is to be kept warm in the oven after baking, cover with foil to keep onion rings from burning.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown 2 pounds ground chuck.
Add 2 large cans of pizza sauce and cheese soup.
Mix and then add mushrooms and the drained noodles.
Mix.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan (or larger).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take out of oven and sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to oven, uncovered, until cheese melts.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Roll out half the dough and line 9 inch pie pan.
In a large saucepan combine water, apples and cranberries.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and walnuts. Cook until mixture thickens and boils.
Pile mixture into pie plate, dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough and cut into strips.
Arrange in lattice design over filling and seal to bottom pastry.
Brush top with milk, sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
1 9 inch pie.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Combine vegetables in large saucepan and cook until tender. Melt oleo in medium saucepan; stir in flour until smooth. Add milk; stir constantly. When mixture becomes thick, add cheese and stir until melted. Add vegetables and pepper. Mix well. Heat thoroughly. If soup is too thick, add more milk.

title: brown sugar crumb cake
directions: Work together brown sugar, flour and shortening until grainy. Remove 1 cup for top crumbs and put aside.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pan.
Add remaining crumbs across top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes one (8 or 9-inch) cake or 2 dozen cupcakes. Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburger cheese pie
directions: Lightly grease 2 (8-inch) pie pans or one large pie pan.
Cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain and add salt and pepper. Spread into pans.
Sprinkle cheese on top.	Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beef and cheese.	Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread slices with butter.
Place buttered side down in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, stirring to crumble.
Spoon over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Put scallops in a saucepan with sherry, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Drain, reserving 1 cup broth.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add reserved broth and heavy cream. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in cheese and scallops.
Put in 6 shells or a shallow baking dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake in a preheated hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: deviled puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, heat water and butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed, golden brown and dry.
Remove puffs to wire rack; cool away from draft.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions, bell pepper and onion tops; saute for about 30 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of celery soup with 1 can of water.
Stir and cook until thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/4 teaspoon red pepper and 1/2 tablespoon paprika, then add shrimp (which makes its own water). Cook until thickens again.
Serve over rice.
Delicious.

title: old time stack cake
directions: Beat Crisco, light brown sugar, eggs and vanilla with mixer until light and fluffy.
Then, by hand, stir in flour,
salt, soda and cinnamon that have been sifted together.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: danish pudding(don't mind the calories)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, orange juice and rind.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in dates and nuts. Pour in large greased and floured stem pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
As soon as pudding comes from oven, pour over it a mixture of 1 cup orange juice, grated rind of 1 orange and 1 cup sugar mixed until sugar is dissolved.
After adding sauce, allow pudding to cool before removing from pan. Store in tightly covered container.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add liquid to make a soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot stew or any hot broth.
Be sure it is boiling when dropping in dough.
Steam covered for 10 minutes.
Plenty of broth is needed for successful dumplings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat condensed milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise; remove all seeds and veins.
Steam, covered, in simmering water for about 10 minutes, until tender. Meantime, cook macaroni; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Place peppers on cookie sheet and fill with macaroni and cheese.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese; sprinkle with paprika and place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute peppers and onions.
Add ground beef or chicken (browned).
Add garlic, drained tomatoes, salt, red wine vinegar, oregano and cumin.
Fry together.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: heather's cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough
into rectangles on a lightly floured surface. Spread with butter.
Mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up tightly; pinch edges and seal well.
Cut into slices (1 1/2-inches thick).
Place in muffin cups; let rise until double, for 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla and spread over rolls.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: wine-braised brisket
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Chop onion and garlic.
Combine onion, garlic, wine and 1/2 cup water in roasting pan.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper; put in pan, fat side up.
Cover and cook in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
For tender brisket, the liquid should just simmer, never boil.

Reduce the oven temperature if necessary. Cut carrots in approximately 1/2-inch slices and add to pan. Cover and cook until the meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours longer. Slice the meat and serve with the carrots and the braising liquid.

title: strawberry dessert(serves 10)
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, pecans and melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes in an ungreased pan, stirring a few times.
Cool and spread 2/3 crumbly mixture in a 12 x 9-inch oblong pan.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half.
Mix flour, cayenne pepper, salt, paprika and garlic salt together.
Put oil in frying pan.
Fry chicken pieces until about done (10 to 20 minutes).
Take out and put in ovenproof pan.
Mix sauce and hot sauce together.
Baste chicken with sauce mixture.
Put in 350° oven until it starts to get crispy, 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn over and repeat.
Take out and enjoy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk gradually.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Alternate layers of potatoes which have been peeled and thinly sliced. Sprinkle lightly with additional salt and pepper.
Pour sauce mixture evenly over potatoes and onion.
Bake at 240° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 2-quart covered dish.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, flour and nuts together and press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Fold in about 10 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Mix instant pudding with milk until it starts to thicken.
Spread evenly over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until crust is brown and filling is slightly puffy. Cool on wire rack.

title: baked ziti with 3 cheeses
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl blend Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, parsley, garlic, pepper and nutmeg; stir in ziti.
Spoon into prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake until top is golden, about 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, then the dry ingredients all mixed together.
Beat well in the creamed mixture.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out on floured surface to thickness desired.
Cut with round or shaped cookie cutters. Grease cookie sheet and place cookies on it and bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken piccata
directions: In plastic bag, combine 1/3 cup flour and paprika.
Add chicken a few pieces at a time.
Shake to coat.
In large skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in margarine; remove from pan. Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Gradually add cream, water and bouillon; over low heat, cook and stir 5 minutes or until bouillon is dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice and sherry; add chicken.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Top with cheese.
Serve with rice; garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: cheese soup
directions: Finely chop vegetables; food processor works well for this. Cook vegetables in butter in covered saucepan over low heat until tender.
Slowly stir in flour.
Gradually stir in broth.
Cook over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Slowly stir in milk, then add cheese gradually.
Continue to heat over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Do not let it boil!
Soup is ready when cheese has melted and soup is medium-hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup of sugar.
Stir in flour, pecans and vanilla.
Shape into small (1 teaspoon) balls and place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 12 to 16 small cookies.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine and simmer tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, chili powder and garlic powder 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, rice, chestnuts, pepper and onions.
Put half of the margarine in the dish and add mixture.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces on top and pour margarine over that.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Turn chicken over halfway through baking.
If needed, add 1/2 can of milk or water to soup as needed.
Cover with foil the last 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add grits and salt to boiling water and cook according to package directions. Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Grease bundt or angel food cake pan real well.
Scatter a few nut meats around the pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Scatter more nuts on top.
Then scatter sugar over nuts; pudding on top.
Melt a cube of butter and pour over all.
Let stand all night.
Bake in the morning for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Spread pecan halves over the bottom of the unbaked pie shell. Beat the eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour filling over pecans in shell. Bake 10 minutes in hot 450° oven.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer.

title: mom's chess pie
directions: Cook raisins in water (enough to cover) about 5 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add sugar, butter, flour, milk, slightly beaten egg yolks and nuts to the pan of raisins and continue to heat over low temperature until mixture thickens.
Pour into previously baked pie shell.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: easy stir 'n' roll biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Measure oil, then milk into one measuring cup (don't stir together).
Pour all at once over flour mixture.
With a fork, mix to make soft dough that rounds up into a ball.
Turn dough onto a sheet of wax paper; knead lightly, without additional flour, 10 times or until smooth.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add milk and water.
Dip bread slices in the mixture and fry on a hot greased griddle until golden brown.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: muddys praline candy
directions: Mix all together, except nuts.
Cook and stir over low heat until soft ball stage.
Add pecans and beat until thickens.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
This is a favorite of my mother.

title: double good macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the package.
Drain well. Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl and mix until well blended. Fold in macaroni. Spoon into a well-greased 10-cup baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it bubbles. This makes 8 servings.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Add soy sauce, Tabasco and pecan halves; blend well.
Cook over low heat.
Add salt.
Place pan in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: moist white coconut cake
directions: Make any white box cake as directed and bake.
Cool 15 minutes and use handle of wooden spoon to poke holes over cake.
Mix milk, sugar and 2 cups coconut.
Mix together, stirring constantly, over heat until mixture boils for 1 minute.
Spoon over cake holes.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: turtles
directions: Boil sweetened condensed milk in its own can for 4 hours.
Mix with pecans and dip in chocolate.

title: the alligator
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve in beverage glass.

title: sunken kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with parchment paper or grease them lightly with butter or vegetable oil.
Sift the flour, soda and salt into a small bowl; set aside.
Using an electric mixer on medium speed, cream the butter, brown sugar, 1/4 cup granulated sugar, peanut butter and vanilla in a medium size mixing bowl until light and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stop the mixer twice to scrape the bowl with a spatula.
Add the egg.
Blend on medium speed until it is almost incorporated, about 10 seconds. Scrape the bowl.
Add the dry ingredients on low speed and blend 15 seconds.
Stop the mixer to scrape the bowl and beaters, then blend until the dough is smooth, about 5 seconds more.
Measure out 48 rounded teaspoonfuls of the dough and roll them into balls using your hands.
Dip one side of each ball in the remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Place them 2 inches apart, sugar side up, on the prepared cookie sheets.
Bake until cookies are light gold, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove cookie sheets from the oven.
Immediately top each cookie with a kiss, flat side down, pressing kiss firmly into the center of the cookie to imbed the kiss.
Carefully remove the cookies from the sheets and place them on a plate or cooling rack. Makes 48 cookies.

title: clam-vegetable soup
directions: Melt margarine in heavy 4-quart kettle or Dutch oven.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery and saute, stirring 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups hot water, the clam juice and herbs.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.
Add onions and corn and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Add clams with liquid and heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: walnut-raisin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aisde.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add egg and orange juice; beat well.
Add 1/3 cup of flour mixture; beat until smooth. Mix in remaining flour mixture and the pineapple.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.

title: salsa dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with salsa.
Spread in shallow dish (about 9-inch).
Top with lettuce, tomato and black olives. Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Makes the same amount as store bought can.
Best part of this recipe is that you can't tell the difference.

title: camper's favorite pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into large bowl or crock.
Combine lime and water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Wash through 5 waters.
Place cucumbers in large kettle.
Make solution of sugar, vinegar, salt, cloves, allspice and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let soak for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil. Cook for 30 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.
Spices may be tied in a bag and discarded before jars are filled if so desired.
These are sweet pickles.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Mix well and put in ice cream freezer.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together beans, onion, corn syrup, garlic, mustard and salt until well mixed.
If desired, arrange bacon strips on top.
Bake in a 400° oven 1 hour until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poppycock
directions: Toast pecans on buttered cookie sheet at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Let cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries and let stand until firm. Then add whipped cream.

title: half and half bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add oil, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Place both flours in large bowl.
Stir milk mixture into flours.
Mix well and turn onto floured board.
Knead until smooth and satiny, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in clean oiled bowl; turn to oil top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double (1 hour).
Punch down and knead briefly.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in oiled loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until double (45 minutes).

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in milk and pumpkin.
Cook in double boiler for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in 1/4 cup sugar and spread on top of pie.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until meringue is firm and brown.

title: green stuff
directions: Put in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until whipped. Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: creamy chicken cheese
directions: Place equal amount of grilled chicken on crescent rolls. Place shredded cheese over chicken.
Roll crescent rolls up and place in oven at 350°.
Put one cup milk, one can of cream of chicken soup and remaining shredded cheese in medium boiling pan and cook until cheese is melted and ingredients become gravy while stirring well.
Bake crescent rolls until done or golden brown. Pour gravy over crescent rolls and enjoy.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: mock chili rellenos casserole
directions: Remove seeds and membranes from peppers; split and lay flat in lightly greased casserole.
Grate cheese over peppers.
Beat eggs; mix in milk, Bisquick and salt.
Pour over cheese and peppers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In same bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour over crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Check with knife into center to come out clean.
Cool. Cut into 24 squares.
Serve garnished with whipped cream. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy southern egg nog
directions: In a large bowl, mix yolks of eggs well, adding sugar gradually and stirring in whiskey slowly.
Stir mixture constantly.
Whip cream until stiff, then fold into egg yolk and sugar mixture.
Fold beaten egg whites into mixture last.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and curry.
Add melted butter to fruit.
Add sugar mixture to fruit.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour over top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in order given.
Add flour, nuts and raisins.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed an box. Pour 1/2

of the mixture in 9 X 13 greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Melt caramels with margarine. Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Dab the rest of the cake batter on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes and 10 more minutes at 250°.

title: wild blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
While oven is heating, melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.

title: oriental salad
directions: Use Top Ramen flavoring packet with oil and vinegar to make dressing.
Mix with rest of ingredients.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender and mix to the desired texture.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix cornstarch, pineapple juice and sugar and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and mix in pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into crust.
Top with pecans and cook at 325° until done.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream together the cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mold around stuffed olives.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: tasty chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients, then add olive oil and dressing. Toss well and chill.

title: cajun shrimp okra gumbo
directions: First, make a roux.
Pour the oil in the bottom of the pot. After the oil is well heated over a low fire add flour.
Cook the flour very slowly stirring almost constantly.
Cook about 45 minutes.
The flour must be browned to a very dark brown.
Add okra, onion, and cook 30 minutes.
Add shrimp then stir in 2 quarts water. Cook for one hour on medium heat.
Salt & pepper to taste.

title: pork chops annette
directions: Brown pork chops; top with sliced onion.
Add the soup, ketchup and Worcestershire.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon, remove from pan and fry onion, then add flour, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar and the water.
Dice and add broiled potatoes.
Heat until hot.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and let stand overnight in fridge.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes and uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: dark bread
directions: To water, add sugar, salt, molasses and Crisco.
Add flour and knead well.
Let raise double in size.
Cut into the size you want your loaves, but this will make 3 regular size loaves. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Very good with cheese on.

title: champagne punch
directions: Dilute orange
and
lemon concentrate with ice water in punch bowl.
Before
serving,
add
well chilled champagne and garnish with orange slices.

title: roast pork
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season the meat.
Place fat side up on rack in roasting pan.
Insert a meat thermometer through the outside of the fat into the thickest part of the meat.
Roast 40 minutes per pound; meat thermometer should register 185°.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese if desired.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: almond grape salad
directions: Wash grapes.
Combine sour cream, brown sugar, and almond extract.
Mix well.
Pour over grapes.
Toss to coat.
Stir in pecans.
Chill, covered overnight for best flavor. Serves 6.

title: dill and sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled new potatoes in boiling, salted water to cover 15 minutes or until tender; drain and let cool to touch.
Cut potatoes into eighths, leaving skins on.
Place in a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and next 4 ingredients; add to potatoes, tossing gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Garnish with fresh dill weed sprig.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Stir together.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Very, very rich!

title: basil pesto
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients into blender.
Add the olive oil slowly.
Heat.
Add some cream.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Drain
juice
from
cans of fruit.
Cut fruit into bite size pieces and combine in bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Season with salt and liquid hot pepper to suit your taste.
Spread refried beans in a shallow pan.
Top evenly with meat.
Sprinkle green chiles over meat. Cover evenly with cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.
(Cover and chill if made ahead.)
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until hot throughout.
Remove from oven; top with green onions and ripe olives.
In the center, mound avocado dip and top with sour cream.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 375° until done.
Frost with pineapple, granulated sugar and butter or oleo.
Cook until thickened.
Cool cake and frosting.
Spread on both layers.

title: venison stew
directions: Heat oil in a large pot, brown meat. Add onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and water. Simmer, covered one hour or until meat is tender. Add potatoes and carrots and cook till tender about 30 to 45 minutes. Mix flour and 1/4 cup of water, add to stew. Cook until it thickens. Remove bay leaf. Eight to ten servings.

title: busy day lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Combine spaghetti sauce with water.
Beat egg lightly.
Combine with cottage cheese.
In large, oblong, glass dish, alternate layers of sauce, uncooked noodles, cottage cheese mixture and cheese slices, forming 2 complete layers and topping with sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap and heat on High for 8 minutes.
Then set power level on 50 percent and cook 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, turning bowl after 15 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and let stand, covered, 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes or 300 strokes. Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with honey, sweetened baked apple and cream.
Freezes well.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender; set aside to cool.
Line crust with bacon and shredded cheese.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, spices and onion.
Pour into crust.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into cakes.
Fry in butter or margarine until brown on each side.
Makes 6 to 8 cakes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Measure and stir dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in blender and add to other ingredients.
Grate zucchini in blender a small amount at a time. (Put in with water and drain in sieve.)
Put in bowl with dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 2 pound coffee can, shortening can or 2-quart mold.
Place can in crock-pot.
Cover with 8 paper towels.
Cover and bake on high 3 to 4 hours or more.
Can bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: microwaved cranberry glog(served hot)
directions: In a 2-quart glass measure or bowl, place cranberry juice, orange juice, raisins, sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves; stir to blend.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes or until heated through.
Remove cloves and ladle juice and raisins into 4 mugs.
Garnish each with an orange slice and a cinnamon stick.
Serves 4.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Remove skin from potatoes.
Shred potatoes in large bowl. Saute onions in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in undiluted soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and shredded cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes, drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked cherry cheesecake
directions: Roll graham crackers into fine crumbs (between 2 sheets waxed paper).
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Add powdered sugar and melted butter.
Mix together and pat into bottom of pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour over crumb crust and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with cherry or other pie filling.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: souper burgers
directions: Brown beef and onions in oil.
Mix soup with seasonings and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
A 10-inch covered skillet works well for this.
Yields 4 servings.

title: aunt lois' banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with low-fat spray.
Stir together flour, soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add egg substitute, sugar, applesauce and skim milk; stir to blend.
Stir in bananas and pecans.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
For easier slicing, wrap loaf and store overnight in a cool place.

title: banana-orange junior
directions: Pour milk and orange juice into blender container.
Scoop in 1 cup of sherbet.
Peel banana and break it into the container. Cover and blend on high speed for 10 seconds.
Pour into glasses. Top each with a scoop of sherbet from the remaining 1 cup.
Yields 3 servings, approximately 1 1/4 cups each.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Have the chicken breasts boned, skinned and cut lengthwise. Pound with a meat hammer until it is a thin cutlet.
Season with salt.
Chill 1/4 pound butter.
Cut the butter into 8 sticks. Place stick of butter at the end of each chicken cutlet (sprinkle some chives on it if you like) and roll up as a jelly roll, being sure to tuck in the sides.
Coat each roll in flour.
Dip into beaten egg, then roll in white bread crumbs.
Roll again in beaten egg and then in bread crumbs.
Make sure the ends are sealed well. Chill before cooking.
Fry chicken rolls in deep hot fat at 375° for about 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
When done correctly, hot butter squirts out when chicken is cut.

title: jewel's fruit cake
directions: Chop and mix fruit, etc.
Sift flour and put 1/2 on fruit and stir until coated.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix with liquid ingredients.
Add fruit and stir in well.
You may cook it in 1 tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out on cloth.

title: cheddar cheese casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and crumble.
Add chopped onion.
Mix cream cheese, soup and margarine.
Stir into potatoes and onion.
Top with Cheddar cheese, shredded, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: single pie crust #1
directions: Stir salt and oil into flour.
Form into ball, flatten slightly and place on sheet of wax paper.
Place another sheet of wax paper on top of dough and roll out quickly.
Peel off top layer of paper and invert into pie plate.
Makes 1 crust.

title: radiatori(four color pasta)
directions: Cook pasta and drain, but do not rinse.
Return immediately to the pot and add the Parmesan cheese, oil, vinegar and spices. Toss until smooth and add steamed broccoli.

title: muskatrola
directions: Season to
taste with salt, black and red pepper.
Cook ground meat
in
skillet
with
only 1 tablespoon fat added to keep from sticking
to
skillet.
Cover
and cook until done. Use meat fork and
break	into
small
bits.
Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until
done
and
drain
off	all water. Cook onions in skillet.
Add
1 tablespoon fat to start onions cooking.
Cover with lid
and cook slowly until tender.
After meat, macaroni and onions are cooked separately, mix together in
a
large pan
or roaster.
Add
mushrooms,
tomato
soup, pimentos, cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Heat in electric roaster or oven until cheese has melted.	Serve hot.

title: all-weather divinity
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Place over high heat, stirring frequently.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks are formed.
(It is much easier to use a self-standing mixer than a hand-held model.)
Continue cooking syrup mixture until, when dribbled from a spoon into cool water, a thin thread is formed and breaks when pinched.
Turn mixer on and slowly add syrup; be careful not to cook egg whites.
Continue to beat mixture as it cools.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating and add pecans when mixture thickens enough to hold onto a spoon without any dropping.
Using two teaspoons, dip onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.
Makes 50 to 60 pieces.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 1/2-inch).
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add cubed Velveeta and mix until melted.
Add oregano and spread on party rye.
Add shredded Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. May be frozen before baking.
If frozen, bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Using an 8-inch tin, set your graham crackers in tin, 1 layer at a time.
Make your chocolate pudding according to box and spread on crackers, layer by layer.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut in squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: twenty-minute beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
While noodles are cooking, prepare sauce blend package using 1 cup beef.
Heat until hot, about 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Drain noodles, pour sauce over noodles and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh raspberry dessert
directions: The coarsely crushed pretzels should be the texture of chopped nuts.
Mix together the pretzels, 3 Tbsp. powdered sugar and melted margarine.
Press this mixture into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Beat together the cream cheese, egg and 1 c. powdered sugar; fold in 9-oz. Cool Whip. Spread mixture on pretzel crust and chill.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin and 1 c. sugar in boiling water; add cold water.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in the raspberries.
Spoon the berry mixture over the cream cheese and chill well before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off bone and put in bottom of baking dish. Reserve broth.
Mix soups, melted oleo and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Use 1 package Stove Top stuffing or use cornbread and make stuffing.
Use broth to moisten and put over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If you use Stove Top stuffing only use part of seasoning, then taste.
Cornbread and loaf bread are better and season as for dressing.
Use enough bread for about 2 cups broth.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Combine pumpkin, salt and spices.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 (5 ounce) custard cups and set in baking pan.
Pour hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Break eggs into large bowl. Beat slightly. Add meat, green pepper and onion.
Mix.
Add milk, catsup, dry mustard and salt. Mix again.
Add bread crumbs and stir. Shape into oval shape. Turn into a greased loaf pan. Spread meat with another 1/2 cup catsup. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Pour juice off and serve.

title: heavenly kraut chops
directions: Grill pork chops.
Combine in crock-pot the sauerkraut, chops, peeled and sliced apple and brown sugar.
Cook for 24 hours in crock-pot.
Delicious.

title: ranch salad
directions: Mix in large bowl; add dressing and top with grated cheese.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart rectangular casserole dish.
Add peaches that are sliced thin.
Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Pour over peaches.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup sugar over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve hot with ice cream.

title: peppermint ice
directions: Slowly melt almond bark in an aluminum saucepan or 2 minutes in microwave. Remove from heat. Add the peppermint extract. Slowly stir in crushed peppermints.
Spread onto a lightly greased cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Let it sit until it hardens. Break into bite size pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 1/2 to 2 pounds of ice.

title: bayou seafood gumbo
directions: In kettle or crock-pot, cook onion in butter until tender. Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water.
(If using fresh shrimp, cook shrimp until pink in color.
Drain, rinse, peel and cut in half.) Add soups, chicken broth, shrimp, crab and clam meats to onion.
Add 1 tablespoon Cajun seasoning.
Heat to almost a boil, then add okra with its liquid and bring to a full boil. Reduce heat.
Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of Cajun seasoning. Simmer gently for 10 minutes. Add cayenne pepper (optional), simmering for 5 more minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal and let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Cream together sugars and shortening. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture. Add the oatmeal and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well in large bowl.
Fold in nuts. Pour into two 9-inch deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Some oven times may vary.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and carrots and cook until tender.
Drain excess water.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in large baking dish. Add the already cooked rice, then add tomatoes.
(Sausage must be cooked and drained.)
Add sausage (mix into mixture).
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbling.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple (juice included) with pudding mix.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Keep frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with hands the powdered sugar, graham crackers, peanut butter and butter.
Roll into small balls and lay aside.
Melt wax.
Roll balls in chocolate chips, then dip into melted wax. Have fairly large sheet of wax paper spread out to lay balls on after dipping in wax.

title: squash elegante
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the dressing.
Line casserole with dressing, then add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook together the broccoli, onion and water until tender. Melt butter on medium heat; add slowly to mix well. Add salt and pepper. Slowly add milk; cook on medium heat until smooth, stirring constantly. Add chicken broth and American cheese. Continue cooking until melted. Add prepared mustard. Add mixture to the cooked broccoli and onions. Continue cooking until all blended.

title: huge chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Cake will fall if door is opened before time is up.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie(originally from england in 1700's)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream the butter and sugar until no trace of graininess remains.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and beat hard.
Add vinegar and beat again.
Turn into unbaked pie shell; bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
The sugar rises to the top and forms a light brown crust when done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chili pepper, nuts or bacon bits. Makes 2 balls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball.
Eat with your choice of crackers.

title: three meat loaf
directions: Combine in a bowl the ground meats, green onions, parsley, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, rosemary, nutmeg and eggs.
Mix thoroughly with the hands.
Shape into a loaf.
Arrange a layer of bacon or salt-pork strips in an earthenware baking dish or casserole and put the meat loaf on top.
Top with a few strips of bacon or salt-pork and bake uncovered in a 325° F. oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
This is delicious hot but even better if weighted down and served cold, when it resembles a good "pate d champagne" of the French provinces.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sinful potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, green onions and 1 cup cheese in a lightly greased deep 3-quart casserole. Gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and the crumbs. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes (longer if refrigerated). Makes 10 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Beat in milk and yeast mixture.
In large bowl of food processor, combine 3 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and the salt.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Transfer to bowl, if using food processor. Stir in yeast mixture and lemon peel.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes.
Stir in about 1/4 cup flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead, adding flour only if necessary to prevent sticking, until dough is smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover tight and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
After removing from refrigerator, let dough stand at room temperature a few minutes, pressing with hands to warm and soften slightly.

title: heather's famous four-bean chili
directions: Mix well, add 1 or 2 cans of water, cover & crock all day (6-8 hours on high, 8-12 hours on low).

Can also be done faster in stockpot on top of stove, but stir very often as it has a tendency to stick. Serve over spaghetti noodles with cheddar cheese, sour cream, onions & tortilla chips on the side.

title: continental flair frosting
directions: Combine sugar and cream in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat; stir constantly.
Remove.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and stir until melted.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Lay steak strips flat on cutting board.
Drape with 2 slices bacon lengthwise; place chopped onion along bacon.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Cut in half across bacon.
Roll jelly roll style from small end and secure with 2 toothpicks.
Fry and brown very well in butter in large skillet.
Transfer to pot. Deglaze skillet with red wine or water and add to pot with pigs; add water to cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Thicken stock with flour. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 7-inch baking dish and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread cracker crumbs on top. Cook for an additional 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry sausage to remove excess fat.
Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons of butter until golden brown.
Pour remaining 1/4 cup of butter in cake pan.
Toss cooked noodles in butter.
Cover noodles with 1/2 of pizza sauce.
Add in order listed:
1/2 grated Swiss cheese, 1/2 sausage, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and all of mushrooms and onion.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with remainder of Swiss, sausage and finally the Mozzarella cheese. Pour pizza sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: Heat water to boil and add bouillon cubes, potatoes and onion. Cook until almost tender.
Add frozen vegetables and soup. Bring back to a low boil and simmer until vegetables are about tender.
Add cheese and simmer about 10 minutes to blend flavors. Soup can be cooked ahead of time, up to adding the cheese. Reheat, add cheese and simmer.
Stir often with wooden spoon during simmering since cheese tends to stick to the bottom.

title: betty's tomato shell salad
directions: Prepare macaroni; cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over macaroni; toss well.
Cover and chill.
Stir again before serving.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish in a 350° oven. Stir in crushed pretzels, spreading evenly in dish.
Bake 10 minutes. Cool.

title: charlie rich's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan which has been heated with oil.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: oreos and milk
directions: Pour whole milk into glass.
Be sure to leave 2 to 3 inches from top.
Crumble up Oreos into glass.
Use spoon to eat.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Place bacon in a medium saucepan and cook until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in saucepan.
Drain and crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until transparent; stir in bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat and add other ingredients.
Blend all ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes. Enjoy!

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk gradually, then add vanilla and Grape-Nuts in buttered baking dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup pecans.
Roll in remaining pecans and chill.

title: flan pan pudding cake
directions: You will need one flan pan.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Put into ice cream freezer, either electric or crank style.
Freeze until firm.
Very yummie!

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a large saucepan for 3 minutes.
While hot, add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well. Spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: roman sponge
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat to consistency of whipped cream.
Add flavoring to whipped cream and fold into jello.
Add macaroons, nuts and salt.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken pie delight
directions: Cook chicken and take off bones; save broth.
In saucepan, put celery soup, peas, milk, minced onion and chicken (chicken should be cut up).
Heat until soup is blended.
Mix together 2 boxes stuffing with melted butter and some broth (stuffing should not be real wet, just wet enough to pat around bottom and little bit up sides).
Into that, pour soup mixture.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain, then add butter and all but 1 cup cheese.
Mix well; add eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: fish and shrimp bake
directions: Place shrimp and fish in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over fish mixture.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lo-cal lo-fat cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake in a well greased 8 by 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Slice and serve warm.

title: upside-down ham and spinach quiche
directions: In bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate, blend spinach, cheese, ham and onion; press lightly.
In medium bowl, combine cracker meal and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add eggs and milk; beat until blended.
Pour over spinach mixture, spreading evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: roy depriest's pickled grilled turkey
directions: Butter turkey and season with salt and pepper.
Grill on covered grill until done.
Place on large platter and pick apart. Mix vinegar, water and red pepper seed.
Pour over turkey.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles until tender. Add meat, noodles, corn, sour cream, soup and pimentos together.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish. Top with crackers and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 1, 2, 3 brownie pie
directions: Mix together margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Combine all ingredients; beat 1 minute and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli, cauliflower mix
directions: Remove tough stems from broccoli and cut into bite size pieces.
Cut cauliflower the same size.
Rinse a few times in cold water, then let stand in cold water 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain well. Add frozen peas, onion and dressing.
Mix well; refrigerate overnight.

title: crullers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan bring the milk and butter to a slow boil.
Add salt (NaCL) and heat until the butter is melted.
Remove pan from heat.
With a wooden spoon, beat in the flour until well mixed and batter rolls away from sides of pan.
Transfer to bowl of electric mixer and beat at medium speed. Add the eggs, 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in chives.
Drop mixture by the teaspoonful onto parchment-lined cookie sheet.
Bake for 35 minutes or until nicely browned and puffed.
(If you remove from oven too soon, the Gougere will collapse.)
Yields 64.

title: pecan shortbreads
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Cover; chill 20 minutes or until dough is slightly firm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream and oil well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Pour half of batter into hot skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over this and add remaining batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, broth and rice.
Top with melted butter and stuffing.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: green fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in quart of tap water. Mix in Kool-Aid and dissolve well. Pour in juices and ginger ale.
Stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: baking powder biscuits(makes 30 biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a very large bowl, combine all the ingredients, except the shortening and buttermilk.
With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in the center and pour in the buttermilk.
With a fork, quickly and lightly combine the ingredients.
Not all of the flour will be used.
Freeze in plastic bags.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Stir sugar thoroughly to room temperature. Let fruit stand 10 minutes so sugar dissolves, stirring occasionally.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla. Beat well.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Spoon pie filling onto dough so that you can cut into squares later and filling is in middle of square.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Sugar will melt over pie filling.

title: fiesta shrimp tacos
directions: Salsa:
Combine Contija cheese, cucumber, onion, tomato, jalapeno pepper, 2 tablespoon oil, lime juice and cilantro. Season with pepper.
Set aside.

title: allsgood pie
directions: When you get your pies mixed, beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.

title: pork tenderloin balsamic(advance prep:  45 minutes.  serves 4.)
directions: First:
Soak white onion in apple cider vinegar in a medium saucepan over very low heat.

title: skillet breakfast
directions: Slice potatoes (with or without skins) thinly.
Cook in large skillet in oil over medium heat.
Turn once, arranging potatoes to cover bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of eggs over crust.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper, onion, chicken and cheese.
Pour remaining eggs evenly over top.
Reduce heat to low so potatoes don't burn. Cover skillet with lid for 15 to 25 minutes until eggs are completely cooked.
Flip onto platter to serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine the brown sugar, honey, margarine and peanut butter. Cook over low heat until mixture bubbles around the edge of the pan.
Pour over the popcorn.
Grease your hands with butter.
Mix popcorn thoroughly and form into balls.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and set aside. Cream confectioners sugar and butter together in a large bowl. After the mixture is creamy, add egg and vanilla.
Mix well, then add the flour mixture that was set aside and mix well. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

Roll out dough on lightly floured surface, cut out and place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and bake 4 to 6 minutes or until bottom of cookies are light brown (if baked too long cookies will get hard).
Bake at 375°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together. Weaken with water and sweeten to taste. Serves 50.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic over medium heat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: orange almond cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Roll into ball shape. Then roll in toasted almonds to coat.
Serve with chocolate wafers or shortbread squares.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl combine first 8 ingredients.
Shape into 4 patties. Fry in skillet over medium heat about 10 minutes or until done. Remove patties.
Add gravy and mushrooms.
Heat until gravy is thick.
Return patties in gravy.
Serve over noodles or potatoes. Really good.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil water and dissolve jello in water.
In saucepan, melt marshmallows and cream cheese.
Add milk, pineapple, pecans and jello mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: people's puppy chow
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter until melted smooth.
Pour over Crispix cereal mix until cereal is well covered.
Put 3 1/2 cups powdered sugar into large plastic bag.
Add coated cereal in bag; shake well.

title: fudge cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and baking powder. Mix in oil, vanilla and milk.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Place all in 10-inch Corning pan.

title: chickpea curry
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan.
Fry sliced onion until golden brown.
Lower heat and add all the spices, the green chilies and fresh coriander.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add water.
Peel and dice potatoes and add this with the chickpeas.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: quick chili and rice
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add spices, corn and green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes
4 servings.

title: karen's krunch kookies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt peanut butter, butter, chocolate and butterscotch chips, then add cornflakes.
Stir until blended together.
Spoon mixture onto cookie sheet to form a ball.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage. Set aside.
Finely chop onion and green pepper. Chop green onions. Cut celery into cross-wise slices about 1/8-inch thick.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Spread into a greased Bundt pan.
Add the berries, then the sugar, then pour the boiling water in.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, grated rind of 1 lemon and juice from 1 1/2 lemons.
Chill mixture thoroughly.
Whip milk, adding juice of 1/2 lemon slowly as it whips.
Fold the chilled mixture into the whipped milk.
Put into ice tray lined with graham cracker crumbs and sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top.
Freeze and serve.
Be sure to have milk really chilled before whipping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
In medium size casserole dish, mix broccoli, soup and 1/3 portion of cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: aunt colleen's chicken casserole
directions: Crumble Ritz crackers in thick layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Place boiled, boned chicken in large bite size pieces over crackers.
Mix soups, broth, sour cream and water chestnuts together.
Layer with crumbled crackers on top.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 325° until golden brown and bubbly around edges.

title: creamy double cheese and bacon macaroni and cheese
directions: Cut bacon up into small pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Put egg into small bowl and beat with fork.
Add milk and beat.
Add the cheese from the dinner and mix thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Clean and soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Add water, ham bone, ground ham, celery salt, and onion.
Cook beans until very soft. Remove bone.
Press remaining meat from bone and add to soup.
Add mustard and onion.
Simmer until the desired tenderness to beans is reached.
Serves: 8 to 10.

title: ezekiel bread
directions: Grind beans and grains into a fine flour.
Mix water, yeast and honey; let sit 5 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a shallow pan; chill. Cut.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer,
then skin, debone and chop.
Save broth to boil spaghetti
in.
Saute
onion
and
celery in one stick of oleo. Add
soup, 1 can of broth, Velveeta cheese, pimento and green pepper.
Cook
until cheese melts.
Stir into spaghetti and chicken.
Mix
well.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes. May need
to
add
broth for desired consistency.
Feeds 10 to 12.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and oregano.
Spread mixture in bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Layer pizza sauce, pepperoni, onion and green pepper on top of cheese mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until bubbly.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).

title: chocolate hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add sugar.
Mix. Add 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix. Beat egg yolks into other 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Add to chocolate mixture and let cook for a few minutes over low heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream, cream puffs, etc.

title: earline's mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Blend all ingredients well so that peppers will be mixed with batter.
Pour 1/2 of dough into greased pan or skillet; put in 1/2 of cheese.
Add remaining dough, then rest of cheese.
Bake slowly at 350° until done.

title: ketchup
directions: Cook tomatoes
soft and juice them.
Put hot juice in a clean white sugar
bag and hang on clothes line and drain 1 to 2 hours. Cut
up
the
onions and cook them.
Force through a sieve in
a large kettle where you plan to cook your ketchup. Add tomato
pulp and
boil 10 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat together oil and eggs.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Gradually add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Turn in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vegetable oil.
Add eggs and beat. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: pork chops-n-apples
directions: This recipe was on the front page of the food section of the "Statesman Journal".

title: holiday pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Quickly add all remaining ingredients.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake in 2 greased (don't flour) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans for 1 hour or 4 (1 pound) greased coffee cans for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
While still warm, brush with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.

title: garden casserole
directions: Place sliced squash, green beans and onion in dish.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat until full.
Crumble bacon on top and pour drippings.
Place sliced tomatoes, cover and cook 45 minutes at 375°.
Place grated cheese on top and melt.

title: spinach salad
directions: Boil 3 cups of water (to save time); put eggs in and bring to a boil until eggs are hard-boiled.
Rinse your spinach thoroughly. Place spinach in boiling water for a minute.
Strain water off spinach.
Place your spinach in a bowl with sliced tomatoes on top and sliced eggs as garnish.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pepper in a cup.
Stir well.
Pour dressing over your salad.

title: southern barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all
the
ingredients in a 3 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil
and
lower
heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 1 quart.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Precook chicken in salted water with whole onion and stalk of celery.
Bone chicken and cut into big chunks.
Combine all ingredients and toss lightly like a salad.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven. Stir after a few minutes of cooking, then cook until set, approximately 30 minutes.

title: eggplant a la riegeldale
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Cook, until done, in small amount of water.
Drain and add all other ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and a little melted butter.
Mix well and put in baking dish (9 x 13-inch is fine for this). Sprinkle with reserved cheese, crumbs and butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine orange gelatin, water, frozen orange juice, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and let chill until partially set.

title: the best biscuits on the planet
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Put dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until it looks like meal.
Stir in almost all of the buttermilk.
If dough is not pliable, add just enough milk to make it soft and easy to roll.
(Too much milk makes dough sticky.
Too little makes the biscuits dry.)

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef; add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Separate biscuits into 12 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups.
Add meat mixture, sprinkle with cheese and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch or 2 baking pans, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat sugar, margarine, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and eggs in a large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, until blended.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Spread 2/3 of batter in jelly roll pan or 1/3 in each square pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls onto pie filling.
Bake until light brown, about 45 minutes.
Drizzle with Glaze while warm.
Cut cake in jelly roll pan into bars, about 2 1/2 x 2 inches; cut cake in square pans into about 2 3/4-inch squares.
Makes 30 bars or 18 squares.

title: mexican supper
directions: Combine beef, milk, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and chili powder in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally. Add flour; stir well.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Stir.
Cover bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with 1 cup of corn chips.
Pour in meat mixture.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: south texas steak
directions: Parboil slowly whole duck and giblets in just enough water to reach half the height of the duck.
Also include desired amount of celery, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Allow this to parboil together for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove duck and place in a roaster; salt and pepper again.
Bake duck slowly at 300°.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and place in a deep dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomato, shredded cheese, black olives and jalapeno peppers.
Serve with taco chips.

title: caramel flan
directions: Fill large pan with water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt sugar in small frypan (shake or stir).
Coat round baking pan with caramelized sugar.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in pan with water.
After baked, turn out on serving dish.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mardi gras pasta
directions: In a 2-quart heavy saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add garlic, green onions, mushrooms, tomatoes and andouille.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are wilted.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and crawfish.
Cook for an additional 2 minutes.
Deglaze pan with white wine and lemon juice and continue cooking until volume of liquid is reduced to 1/2.
Add heavy whipping cream, stirring constantly.
Reduce until cream is thick and of sauce-like consistency, approximately 5 minutes.
Add diced red bell pepper and chipped butter, 2 to 3 pats at a time, swirling pan constantly over burner.
Do not stir with a spoon as butter will break down and separate if hot spots develop in the pan.
Continue adding butter until all is incorporated.
Remove from heat.
Add parsley and season to taste using salt and pepper.
Gently fold in cooked rotini pasta and serve.
May be chilled and served as a cold pasta salad.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of this into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins/nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 this over batter in pan and swirl. Pour remaining batter into pan; sprinkle remaining sugar mixture and swirl.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Top with glaze.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dust work surface with 1/4 c. grated cheese.
Lay unfolded sheet of puff pastry on top of cheese, then sprinkle with 1/4 c. of grated cheese.
Gently roll dough out with a rolling pin, pressing cheese into dough to a thickness of about 1/8-inch.
Dust with more cheese, as needed.
Cut pastry into long 1/2-inch wide strips.
Give each strip several twists, then lay 1/2-inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 10 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: *Can use water, beef or chicken bouillon, water and combination.

title: gringo enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil until cooked or tender.
Place between paper towels.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Mix everything together in casserole dish; bake in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°. (Don't necessarily double noodles if doubling recipe.)

title: deep dish sausage pizza
directions: Bake sausage in oven about 20 minutes; drain and set aside. Squeeze tomatoes to remove juice.
Mix seasonings into squeezed tomatoes.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken. Melt cheese, set aside. Combine soups, water, Rotel tomatoes, and chicken; bring to a boil; remove from heat. Layer chips, cheese and chicken mixture in a large baking dish. Top with cheese; bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: non-milk chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Put in a baked pie crust.
Top with meringue, then brown.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together biscuit baking mix, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Stir in milk.
Drop by rounded tablespoons about 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Make a shallow well in center of each.
Fill with 1 teaspoon of preserves (any flavor).
Bake until golden brown, about 18 to 20 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with Glaze.

title: granny's dumplins
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Knead.
Roll out thin.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Drop in boiling chicken broth slowly to keep boiling.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 12 minutes.

title: homemade scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and salt.
Carefully fold into potatoes.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with cheese. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
I add extra cheese to mine, if available.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream cheese and mushroom enchiladas
directions: Stir undrained tomatoes, honey, cumin, coriander and pepper together in a medium skillet.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Simmer uncovered, about 30 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Cook mushrooms and chili powder in margarine in a saucepan over medium heat for 4 or 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and liquid evaporates.
Reduce heat. Stir in cream cheese until melted.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the sour cream and the green onion.
Spoon 1/3 cup of the cream cheese mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in greased 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Spoon tomato mixture over enchiladas.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with shredded cheese and dollop with remaining sour cream.
Bake, uncovered, for 4 or 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.
Has 338 calories per serving.

title: english muffin snack
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffins) together.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut into squares.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons Crisco shortening in a double boiler until smooth.
Mix all ingredients, except chocolate, and mix in blender.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheets, covered with wax paper.
Dip balls into chocolate mix, using fork to remove.
Replace on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir clam liquid, potatoes, salt and pepper and add to onion.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook until the potatoes are done.
Stir in milk, heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve hot or cool.

title: greek capellini
directions: Cook capellini, drain.
Wash and cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Coat skillet with vegetable spray; add oil.
Over medium heat, add garlic; saute 1 minute, add broccoli; saute.
Stir in broth and Greek seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in tomato and capellini.
Simmer until heated.
Add olives and pepper, toss. Transfer to serving bowl; sprinkle with Feta.
`Contains 3.6 grams fat per serving.

title: no fail sunday pot roast
directions: Season roast and brown well all over.
Cut 3 deep slots into top of roast and put 1 clove into each slot.
Pour vinegar over roast and add water until it comes up halfway the roast.
Cook in pot until well done and tender.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch and enjoy!

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in pan and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown chuck and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream in separate bowl.
Cook spaghetti and layer on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese mixture and then meat.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dippin' for chicken
directions: Mix and chill.
Great for dipping chicken nuggets, cheese puffs, etc.

title: crackle top molasses cookies
directions: Set oven temperature to 350°.
In large bowl, combine oil and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg, beating well.
Stir in molasses, 2 cups flour, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
If necessary, add a little more flour to make firm dough.
Shape dough into 1 to 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in the 1/3 cup sugar.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown and tops crack.
Cool on racks.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, eggs, vanilla and sugars until fluffy.
Next, add flour, oats, salt and baking soda. Batter will become very stiff.
Add milk chocolate chips.

title: south georgia peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches with sugar.
Spread evenly in 8 x 8-inch pan. Combine all ingredients.
Spread over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheatin' fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and peaches together.
Put in pie pan; sprinkle cake mix "dry" all over peach mixture.
Cover with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Add onion, corn, pepper, garlic, spaghetti (or chili) sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer, covered, until sauce thickens, about 30 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, coffee, molasses and raisins.
Add dry ingredients to this and mix well.
If dough is too dry, add a little milk.

title: namasu(japanese cucumber salad)
directions: Slice cucumber very thin and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain.
Press out excess water.
Don't rinse.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix soft butter, vanilla and sifted confectioners sugar together thoroughly.
Sift together flour, chopped nuts and salt; stir in.
Roll up in wax paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick (whichever you prefer).
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown.
Let cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Roll a second time if you like.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage into very fine pieces. Place in a dry dish towel and squeeze to make it tender.
Blend thoroughly with salad oil, vinegar and mustard; pepper and salt to taste.
Chill; serve garnished with thinly sliced cucumbers and sprinkled with paprika.

title: arleen's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine everything but the bread crumbs.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's cornbread
directions: Melt butter in heavy iron skillet in oven while being preheated to 350°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Beat eggs; add milk and 2 tablespoons melted butter from skillet. Quickly stir milk mixture into dry mixture.
Pour batter into remaining butter in skillet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salad nicoise
directions: Line shallow bowl or dish with large outer leaves of lettuce. Break remaining lettuce into bowl and toss with 2 tablespoons French dressing.
Separately season potatoes, beans, tomatoes and tuna with dressing and arrange over lettuce.
Garnish with olives, eggs and anchovies.
