Pour 1/2 to 3/4 cup dressing over all and sprinkle with herbs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: all-season quick loaves
directions: Stir together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
In a medium-sized bowl, lightly beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and oil and stir until blended.
Stir in the vanilla and your choice of fruit or vegetable.
Add the flour mixture all at once and stir just until evenly moist.
Then divide batter evenly between 2 greased and floured 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake bread in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out on a wire rack to cool completely. These breads are easier to slice if they sit at least a day. Wrapped well, they keep, refrigerated, up to a week.
You can freeze them for longer storage.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain well the chopped spinach.
Drain and chop chestnuts; add other ingredients.
Let sit for a few hours before using.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: rose rolls

title: maxine's pineapple and nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, eggs, oil and pineapple. Add last bananas and pecans. Mix with spoon. Cook at 320° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and butter.
Add and mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add and mix baking soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.
Keep adding flour until you can roll the dough into small balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: kindergarten macaroni and cheese
directions: Put cold water in pot.
Put on stove and let it boil.
Put in the macaroni when the water starts boiling.
Leave it about 10 or 20 minutes.
After you pour the macaroni, add the cheese.

title: shepherd's pie casserole
directions: Place carrots in small saucepan; barely cover with water. Cook until fork-tender; drain.
Meanwhile, in separate saucepan, cook onion, barely covered with water, until tender; drain. Combine lamb, vegetables, salt and pepper in 2-quart casserole; mix well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine carrots, turnips, celery and garlic salt.
Arrange on crisp lettuce and serve with dressing.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald the milk and shortening or butter in double boiler or over hot water.
Beat egg yolks (or eggs) and sugar together until light.
Pour scalded milk on the eggs and sugar and stir until well mixed.
Return to boiler; cook until custard coats the spoon, stirring constantly.
Remove at once from heat; cool.
Add vanilla and salt.
Custard must be very carefully cooked.
If not cooked enough, it will be too thin and if cooked too long, it will separate.
It is very delicious served on ice cream or try putting a dip of ice cream in a bowl of custard.

title: pretzel-mint pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and pretzel crumbs.
Press into a 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
When cool, spread ice cream on crust.
Now add fudge sauce; top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with a few pretzels.

title: fran's friend's progressive dinner chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13 baking dish with chipped beef slices. Wrap each chicken piece with 1 strip of bacon. Place on top of chipped beef. Mix undiluted soup, sour cream and sherry and pour over chicken breasts. Bake at 325° for 2 hours. No cover. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cups("easy")
directions: Unwrap candy; set aside.
Cut 1/4-inch slices of cookie dough, then cut those in quarters.
Place the small quartered pieces in a small baking cup.
Place these on a cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on the Pillsbury package.
The dough will rise and be puffy.
As soon as you take them out of the oven, place a peanut butter cup in the center of the dough and press down.
Let cool.

title: wing dings
directions: Mix ingredients; put on one side of wings.
Bake 25 minutes on one side.
Put sauce on other side and bake another 20 minutes.

title: chipped-chopped ham
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook on low in crock-pot all day.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken divine
directions: Heat soup, mayonnaise and cheese to blend.
Lay broccoli on bottom of 13 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Pour sauce over.
Mix butter and bread crumbs; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry filled almond muffins
directions: *To toast almonds, spread on cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Remove casings from sausage; crumble and brown.
Drain off most of fat.
Add celery, zucchini, onions, green peppers and tomatoes. Add remaining spices.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and garlic bread.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 1/3 cup oil.
Remove chicken to loaf pan (skin side up).
Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups.
In saucepan, add sugar, starch, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper slices.
Bake 30 more minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Keeps indefinitely!

title: peach glory
directions: Take one box jello and mix with one cup boiling water.
Stir good and add ice cream.
Stir until melted well.
Pour into dish and chill.
Mix other box of jello with one cup boiling water. Set in icebox until thickens.
Drain peaches.
Place peach slices on ice cream mixture.
Pour second jello mixture over peaches. Cover with Cool Whip before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs until fully incorporated.
In another bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake in 15 x 10 x 2-inch greased pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Ice when cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in blender and mix.
Slowly add oil; add poppy seed and mix slightly.
Makes 1 quart.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack.
Fill and top with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion; sprinkle with salt and toss. Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze slices, discarding liquid. Place slices in bowl. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over cucumbers and mix together. Chill 1 or 2 hours.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Combine oil and butter on medium heat until butter melts.
Add garlic and parsley, cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining seasonings.
Add tomatoes and simmer 30 minutes.
Add anchovies and tomato paste. If adding shrimp add and let simmer 3 minutes.
Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Form in small balls.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: hello dolly
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke quiche(pie)
directions: Beat eggs; add Mozzarella, salt, pepper and parsley.
If frozen, boil artichokes until cooked.
Drain well and brown in oil with garlic.
Pour mixtures into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hearty beans and ground beef
directions: Combine baked beans, lima beans and kidney beans.
Drain all beans in colander.
Cover and bake 40 minutes or cook on low heat in crock-pot 2 to 3 hours.

title: fudge-pudding cake
directions: Combine first 5 dry ingredients sifting three times.
Combine milk, vanilla and margarine; add to flour mixture.
Stir in chopped walnuts or use pecans.
Spread in 6-cup casserole.
It will be thick.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter. Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with ice cream if desired.

title: crab filled croustades
directions: Cut 3-inch rounds from each slice of bread with a 3-inch plain or fluted
cookie cutter.
Press carefully into well-buttered tiny muffin tins (about 2 inches wide; these usually come in panels of 12).
Bake in preheated 400°
oven for about 10 minutes, until rims are lightly browned.
Fill with the following:

title: salisbury steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, melt butter and cook onion.
In a large bowl, beat together 1/3 cup of soup and egg. Stir in bread crumbs and salt.
Let crumbs soften about 5 minutes. Add cooked onion and beef.
Mix well.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Add water and beat with rotary eggbeater for 2 minutes.
Pat dry excess moisture from hot dogs. Dip hot dogs in batter, holding hot dog with a fork.
Drain off excess batter over the bowl.
Fry in hot, deep fat (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: fulton's cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice, peel and vanilla; mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after adding each egg.
Fold in already beaten egg whites.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meats and drain off fat.
Dice cheese and stir with meat until melted.
Stir in rest of ingredients and spread on party rye.
When ready to serve, place under broiler for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: oven brisket
directions: Night before sprinkle with celery salt, onion salt, garlic powder, lemon pepper and liquid smoke.
Sprinkle generously!
Wrap up and seal in foil.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: nestle's fudge
directions: Put in a pan and boil until you think it is done.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and a medium-size can of peanuts.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients, then get out cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes, until light brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate chips and wax, and then form into little balls.
In a double boiler, at the top, melt 3/4 bar of wax and semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Dip 3 or 4 balls at a time with a fork in the wax and chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: becky's salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to salmon liquid to measure 1 cup; set aside.
Melt margarine in pan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute slowly.
Add milk mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake salmon with fork.
Add lemon juice, 1/2 cup corn flakes and white sauce, stirring well.
Refrigerate until chilled. Shape into croquettes.
Roll into remaining corn flakes.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions on box in deep bowl. In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then combine with Dream Whip.
Refrigerate while pie shells cook and cool.
Pack bottoms of pie shells with coarsely chopped pecans. Bake shells at low setting so pecans won't burn.
Pour cream cheese mixture into shell after they have cooled.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and salt. Add sugar; beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and lemon extracts. Blend flour and milk alternately. Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan. Put in cold oven at 300°. Bake 1 1/2 hours. Do not peek!

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger, noodles, sauce, mushrooms and pepper.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese over top.
Place pepperoni on cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips; marinate in Italian dressing overnight.
Remove chicken strips from marinade; roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes - a new way
directions: Wash new potatoes and slice about 1/8-inch thick. Add cooking oil, soup mix and red pepper. Shake well to coat potatoes. Place in greased casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake in 450° oven until almost done. Remove foil the last few minutes of cooking time. Serve hot.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and paprika in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with butter.
Cover.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: chinese no bake cookies
directions: Melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips over low heat. Slowly add the noodles.
Stir carefully.
Spoon drop them onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.

title: chili con queso
directions: * Or if not available in your area, substitute 1 cup of picante sauce.

title: mashed potatoes with crimini mushrooms
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain potatoes and leave over medium heat until excess moisture evaporates (approximately 1 minute); remove from heat.
Add 5 tablespoons butter and mash well.
Add milk until reaches desired consistency.
Season with salt and pepper.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Add half of mushrooms; saut until beginning to soften (approximately 3 minutes).
Add remaining mushrooms and shallots.
Saut until juices evaporate and mushrooms brown (approximately 12 minutes); season with salt and pepper.
Mix 2/3 of mushrooms into potatoes.
Put in bowl and top with remaining mushrooms.
Sprinkle with chives.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: white chili
directions: Simmer all spices and liquids for 30 minutes, then add chicken and beans.
Simmer 10 minutes, then garnish with cheese.

title: cold cucumber soup 1
directions: Cut up cucumbers and blend all ingredients together.
Serve in chilled glass mugs.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef and sausage in skillet; add water.
Cook until done over medium heat.
Stir and break up meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Spoon onto hamburger rolls (open-face).
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 6 cups of water until done; set aside.
Mix cheese, eggs, sausage, salt and Tabasco to taste.
Mix all together and cook 1 hour.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, milk, seed and raisins.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Start oven at 425°.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Beat egg until frothy; add cream and mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients until just mixed. Pour into muffin pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: butternut souffle
directions: Cook whole squash in water until soft.
Remove and cool.
Cut open and discard seeds and stringy stuff.
Spoon out the meat and mash well.
Mix other ingredients well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set and brown around edges.
Serve warm.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight to improve flavor.

title: blueberry-orange coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine blueberries, sugar and orange rind; toss and set aside.
Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Beat in egg substitute.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine yogurt, orange juice concentrate and vanilla, mixing well.
Add flour mixture alternately with yogurt mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients, beating at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into an 8-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray; top with blueberry mixture.
Sprinkle with crumb topping; bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly on a wire rack; serve warm.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing, oil, lemon pepper, dill weed and garlic powder.
Pour over crackers.
Place in warm oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: On a plate, spread the beans, then the sour cream, picante sauce. Top with the cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Simmer over low heat.

title: orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease twelve medium-sized muffin cups or line with paper liners; set side.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients and orange peel.

Add combined egg, orange juice, butter, milk and vanilla; mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling each cup half full. Bake 18-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Spread with whipped butter and marmalade, if desired.

title: hot pepper jam
directions: You may add 1 teaspoon cayenne for extra hot.

title: cream pie (with variations)
directions: Mix flour, 2/3 c sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell. Spread with meringue made by beating egg whites and cream of tarter until stiff, then beating in 6 T sugar, 1 T at a time. Bake in a 350 F oven 12-15 minutes.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Place berries in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, oleo and salt together with fork and knife or until well mixed. Sprinkle mixture over berries.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In medium saucepan, heat butter, water, sugar and salt to boiling over high heat.
When butter melts, remove pan from heat; add flour.
Beat until smooth over medium heat.
Stir 30 seconds until ball forms. Cool 3 minutes.
Beat in 1 egg at a time, beating until dough is smooth between additions.
Drop dough onto baking sheets; brush with yolk mixture.
Bake dough 25 minutes or until double in size or golden brown.
With knife tip, slit puffs so steam escapes. Lower heat to 325°.
Bake puffs 15 minutes; remove.
To serve, halve puffs crosswise.
Remove soft insides.
Fill with pastry cream.
Cover tops.
Drizzle with warm sauce.

title: nut mallow goodies(candy)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over hot (not boiling) water until chips melt.
Stir until blended; remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and peanuts; mix well.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cool bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Mix together with other ingredients.

title: chocolate streusel squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugars, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread preserves over crust.
Sprinkle evenly with chocolate pieces.
Combine reserved oat mixture and nuts.
Sprinkle over chocolate pieces patting gently.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 375° oven, until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with melted chocolate if desired.
Let chocolate set before cutting into bars.

title: irene's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, then peel.
Chill potatoes, then grate.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add cheese until it almost melts.
Take off heat and add sour cream and onions; salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over grated potatoes and fold carefully until mixed.
Place in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Dot 2 tablespoons of butter on top.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add the beaten eggs. In a separate bowl, make a paste of cocoa and coloring. Add to the cream mixture. Add salt, vanilla, and buttermilk; alternating with flour. Mix well with electric mixer. Fold in soda and vinegar that have been mixed at the last minute. Pour evenly into 3 layer pans or large oblong pan. Bake 25-35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick stir-n-roll biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475° (very hot).
Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup without stirring.
Then pour all at once into flour and stir with fork until mixture cleans sides of bowl.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet or ungreased muffin cups.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 16 biscuits.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Mix everything together; simmer for 2 hours.
Boil jars and lids.
Use one pound meat to 1 pint sauce.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook; they are soft cookies.

title: blueberry-nut crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread undrained pineapple on bottom.
Add berries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over fruit.
Drizzle margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on this.
Add nuts last.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Thaw crab meat and shrimp and retain liquid.
Melt butter. Stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Gradually add half and half.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Combine 1/2 cup hot mixture with egg yolk.
Then add egg yolk mixture to remaining hot mixture; mix well.
Cook an additional 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add crab meat, shrimp and liquid and heat through.
Remove from heat.
Add sherry.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: strawberry-cream squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir occasionally until thawed.
Slice bananas and add to gelatin along with drained pineapple.
Pour half into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, and allspice.
In a separate bowl cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Mix well together the egg, molasses, and water.
Add to the sugar/margarine mixture.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.

title: seven layer tex-mex dip
directions: Mash the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix the mayonnaise and sour cream with taco mix.
Arrange the ingredients in layers in a large, shallow casserole dish, starting with the bean dip.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours to allow flavors to mix. Serve chilled with corn tortilla chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook cream, sugar and syrup to soft ball stage and pour over freshly popped corn.
Dampen hands with cold water and shape into balls.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: cabbage beef bake
directions: Place cabbage pieces into greased baking dish.
Wilt cabbage in microwave approximately 7 minutes.
Saute ground beef and onion.
Put beef over cabbage.
Cover with Ragu or soup.
You may sprinkle with celery salt, garlic salt, chili powder or Aunt Jane's crispy salt.
Bake 1 hour at 500°.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease casserole with 1 tablespoon oleo.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all of the ingredients in a large bowl and mix together very well (dice your onion in small slices).
Pour out in a deep casserole dish and put a thin layer of ketchup on top.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered with aluminum foil.
Take out and remove foil and drain off most of the fat. Put back in and cook for about 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: hot sausage grinders
directions: Cut sausages in 2-inch pieces.
Fry in oil until brown on each side.
Add peppers and onions.
Fry until soft.
Add tomato paste and enough water to cover sausages.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with hard rolls, tossed salad and French fries.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place butter in pan to melt in heated oven. Mix all other ingredients together. Pour part of melted butter into batter. Mix well and bake until brown around edges, about 30 minutes.

title: taco chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips and discard.
Separate wins at the joints. Dip chicken pieces in milk.
Combine taco seasoning and bread crumbs in a plastic bag.
Place two or three pieces of chicken in the bag at a time and shake well.
Place in a 12 x 8 baking dish. Micro cook until chicken is done, about 14 minutes, giving the dish a half turn every 4 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in water and drain.
In saucepan, combine butter, cheese and heavy cream until warm.
Add black pepper, garlic powder and parsley to taste.
Add to cooked and drained noodles. Toss gently.

title: stuffed mushrooms - italian style
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and chop fine.
Remove casing from sausage and put meat in skillet with chopped stems, garlic and 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Cook, breaking up meat with a fork, until lightly browned.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil, parsley and cheese.
Fill mushroom cavities with the mixture, rounding up tops.
Put in shallow baking pan with remaining oil and 1/4 cup of water in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve as an hors d'oeuvre or hot as a first course.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour in half baked pie shell.
Return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Measure 3/4 cup of combined syrup.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add orange rind and measured syrup.
Chill
until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruits.
Pour into mold and chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and garnish.

title: drying herbs
directions: Remove stems and wash fresh picked herbs.
Measure 1/2 to 1 cup loosely packed herbs.
Spread between 2 pieces of paper toweling.
Cook on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until dry and crumbly.
Crumble, if desired, and store in an airtight container.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the boiling water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Transfer the mixture into a glass bottle and let stand for thirty days.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill.
Cut center out of loaf of round limpa bread.
Fill center with dip.
Cube limpa center and pile around loaf.

title: angel food cake supreme
directions: Sift the flour with confectioners sugar 3 times.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, salt, vanilla and almond extract until stiff enough to hold soft peaks, but still moist and glossy. Beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Continue to beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in 1/4 of flour mixture at a time.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 375° about 30 minutes or until done. Invert pan and cool cake thoroughly.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Mix both milks together.
Dip pickles in milk, then in flour; deep fry.
For sauce, use French horseradish, mustard, mayonnaise and garlic salt to taste.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water and ice cubes.
Let set about 3 hours.
Do not use metal container.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chickens until done.
Remove chicken from bones.
Do not use skins, gizzards or livers.
Strain chicken broth.
Put 8 cups of the broth in a very large pot.
Add lima beans, garden peas, finely chopped carrots, mashed tomatoes and chicken which has been chopped into small pieces.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on medium heat, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Reduce liquids about 1 inch by cooking.
Add potatoes that have been cooked and drained.
Add creamed corn and cooked rice.
Turn heat to medium-high and cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
If stew doesn't thicken, add a little white sauce (flour and water).
Remove from heat.

title: chicken encore(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute onion in butter 6 minutes or until golden.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine onion and mushrooms with chicken, bread crumbs, peas, eggs, sage, garlic salt and pepper, tossing lightly until mixed.
Transfer to baking dish.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 40 minutes.
Remove foil.
Spread soup on top and sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until lightly browned.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375° and grease 2 cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites and
salt until soft peaks.
Add sugar slowly and beat until stiff
peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls
onto cookie sheets.
Place in oven and immediately turn oven off. Leave in oven 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: mandarin orange salad and dressing
directions: The dressing can be prepared ahead. Just take it out of the fridge a little before mixing salad. Mix salad at the last minute.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in 3 or 4-quart dish; cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields about 10 to 12 servings.

title: "chicken" lasagna supreme
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In small bowl, combine Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
In large skillet, add margarine or oil and saute mushrooms and onions.
Add Fri-Chik and simmer.
In medium mixing bowl, combine soup, milk and cottage cheese.
Add to sauteed mixture and stir completely. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer noodles, 1/3 mushroom sauce and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat; bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add flour last.
Roll out on floured board to desired shape.
Put in greased pan; let rise for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the sugar, syrup and margarine together.
Cook over a medium heat until butter melts.
Let come to a boil.
Beat eggs. Slowly add sugar mixture to beaten eggs.
Add vanilla flavoring and chopped pecans.
Pour into raw pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 9 bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak.
Rinse and cook.
Add salt and tomatoes; cook until all beans are done.

title: wild rice hot dish(large recipe)
directions: Rinse rice real good before cooking.
Boil until tender.
Cut sausage in chunks and brown with celery, peppers and onions. Rinse rice again and combine with browned sausage mixture in a large baking dish.
Add water and bake about 1 hour or until done (dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube per 1 cup of water).
Stir often and check that there is enough moisture.
When moisture needs to be added, use the water with bouillon dissolved in it.
Very good recipe for a large crowd.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Rub roast with pepper.
Line a pan with aluminum foil.
Place roast on aluminum foil.
Pour dry onion soup mix on top of roast. Mix mushroom soup and milk together and pour over roast.
Add oregano, bay leaves and garlic.
Wrap foil around roast and fold to seal.
Bake at 300° to 350° for about 3 hours.
This makes an excellent gravy to serve with rice.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil peppers and onions slowly with very little water.
Cook until water is gone.
Mix macaroni with onions and peppers.
Add pimento, cheese, soup and mayonnaise.
Place all ingredients in casserole and sprinkle with cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mulberry pie
directions: Put berries in pie shell; mix sugar and cornstarch and put over berries. Sprinkle nutmeg over pie.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut
steak in very thin strips and brown in oil.
Slice green pepper.
Add
broth,
vegetables and soy sauce to meat. Cover; cook
over
low heat about 10 minutes or until tender. Stir often.
Combine
water
and
cornstarch.
Stir into meat mixture. Cook,
stirring
until thickened.
Serve over sticky rice and eat with chop sticks.

title: hot fudge walnut pudding cake(makes about 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In bowl, stir together 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoon cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.

title: banana splitz
directions: Mix together the margarine and graham cracker crumbs and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the pudding according to the package directions and spread over the graham crust.
Layer the pineapple and the bananas over the pudding.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ricky's cookies
directions: Cream butter and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from the end of teaspoon onto a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Yield:
about 150 small cookies.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and
pour over steak.
Let stand for approximately 3 hours before grilling.
Cook over coals to desired doneness.

title: dot's bread or rolls
directions: Mash yeast cake or dissolve package of yeast in lukewarm water in a cup.
Add sugar to yeast and then fill cup with buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour and salt; add shortening, then milk-yeast mixture and enough additional milk to make dough. Knead well.
Let dough rise until doubled, about 2 1/2 hours, then make into rolls or loaf and let rise again, about 1 hour.
Bake loaf for 50 minutes at 400°, rolls 15 minutes at 450°.
Yields 1 loaf or 24 rolls.

title: apple pie
directions: Boil sugar, butter and orange juice until slightly thickened. Add apples to sauce and cook until apples are transparent.
Pour into crust and top with lattice.
Put 1/4 cup sugar over lattice and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes longer or until golden.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Slowly beat in sugar.
Add cream and vanilla. Pour in gallon bucket and finish filling with milk to about 3 inches from top.
Freeze.

title: veggie bars
directions: *I use Watkins garlic and dill snack and dip mix or Watkins cucumber dill seasoning.

title: french cabbage soup
directions: Cook beef and onion.
Cover cabbage and celery in water or beef broth.
Cook until medium done.
Add hamburger and remaining ingredients.
Season to taste with brown sugar, salt and pepper. Simmer until done.

title: bonnie price's own geneva's chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix according to package directions and pour over coconut mixture. Blend softened cream cheese, sugar and milk together. Pour (it will be very thick) over the cake.
You may have to dollop the mixture onto the cake mix. Do not thin it.
Bake 45 minutes (or slightly more) in a 350° oven. Rich!

title: shrimp curry
directions: Put in casserole.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice, pineapple chunks, avocados, apples, peanuts and chutney.
Serves 10 people.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stir in fruit.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate until firm. Store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam cooking spray. Dust with sugar and set aside.

title: chili-cheese souffle
directions: Butter 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Spread 1/2 chiles in dish. Spread thin slices of Jack, rest of chiles and thin slices of Cheddar.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Spoon off fat.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with Twigs and/or potato chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased dish. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: pumpkin icebox pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions and set aside.
Combine pudding, milk, pumpkin and cinnamon.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour in baked or graham cracker pie shell and chill before serving.

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: *Or 1 teaspoon celery salt.

title: elegant beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 2 or 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Dry fillets.
Stir eggs in bowl.
Put bread crumbs, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Dip fillets in egg, then bread crumbs.
Use 11-inch skillet with 1/4-inch oil to fry.
Brown both sides at high temperature, then turn to low temperature to finish frying.

title: charlie brown
directions: Mix and put in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: squash cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine the cornmeal, flour, sage and onions in a bowl.
Stir to mix.
Add squash, egg, milk, and oil.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 10 inch skillet (I prefer an iron skillet). Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: liver nips
directions: Boil beef, liver and suet in 1 quart water, or enough to cover, until well done.
Grate the liver and mash suet together. Combine with seasonings, eggs and flour and add about 1 cup of stock.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling stock (1-1/2 quarts). Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Keep stock boiling and be careful not to crowd dumplings.
This is an old recipe handed down from our German-Deutsch (Dutch) Fork ancestors.
I brought it from South Carolina.

title: easy creamed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables in water until heated. Stir in soup and water or milk.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti with veal and peppers
directions: Brown spareribs in skillet on stove top with butter.
Add salt and pepper for flavor.
Place in roaster with onion slices on top and a little water covering the bottom.
Set in oven at 450° for 30 minutes.
Drain water and add your barbecue sauce on top of each bone.

title: holiday spiced punch
directions: In saucepan, combine water, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes. Chill; remove spices.
To serve, combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
For garnish, float lemon slices in punch.
Makes 12 cups (16 six-ounce servings).

title: veggie bars
directions: Put rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pack down and stick together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (flaky).
Cool.

title: caramel-layer chocolate bars
directions: In saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Cook and stir until caramels are melted.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts. Stir by hand until dough holds together.
(It might be crumbly.)

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add cheese.
Add flour.
Put apples into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab fettucini
directions: Melt margarine and garlic butter together and stir in flour and gradually add the half and half until thickened.
Add the Parmesan cheese and cook and stir until smooth.
Fold in washed and cleaned shrimp and crab meat and heat about 5 to 10 minutes (shrimp will turn pink).
Toss the fettucini with the sauce or just pour some sauce over the fettucini and serve.

title: equal banana cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend oil, eggs, skim milk and vanilla.
Stir in bananas.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until flour is moistened.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) round pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until just done, 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: fresh homemade tomato soup
directions: Chop tomatoes into small pieces.
Saute in oil over medium heat until tender.
Combine tomatoes and chicken stock in blender. Blend until liquified.
Slowly add milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with celery leaves.

title: ripe banana fritters
directions: Mash banana and add sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix baking powder, salt and flour and add to banana mixture.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry on one side until golden brown, then turn with slotted spoon to brown on other side.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Keep fritters warm until all are fried.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: fruited jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: spinach dip #3
directions: Combine soup mix, sour cream and mayo thoroughly.
Light or fat free versions can be used when heavy hors d' oeuvres not required.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator 8 hours to blend flavors.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; chill.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix and drizzle melted oleo over all.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crabmeat and Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Fold in crabmeat.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes, until cheese bubbles and melts.
Delicious.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake and icing
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream shortening with the sugar until light and fluffy; blend in vanilla and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the water.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Add the sauerkraut and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in the pan; spread with icing.

title: nacho dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Place on bottom of baking dish (or microwave dish).
Spread over surface.
Add can of chili.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese is melted. Top with olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: noodles with spicy peanut sauce
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except pasta.
With a wooden spoon, work together until smooth and creamy.
Let mixture stand at least 4 hours.
Toss mixture with cooked and drained noodles or pasta.
(Drain pasta well).
Add a bit of hot oil if pasta has cooled and toss.
Add finely chopped green scallions at the end for zest.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: stuffed peppers and spaghetti
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and let stand for 3 minutes.
Saute onions in oil, add 1/2 of the onions to meat mixture, add the other 1/2 of the onions and seasoning in the tomato sauce.
Simmer halved peppers (seeded) in sauce, covered for 45 minutes.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: chili
directions: Mix hamburger meat, near beer and tomato sauce together and simmer for 40 minutes, then add chili powder, corn flakes, salt and onion and cook for 30 more minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients into a mixture until crumbly.
Put 3/4 of the mixture in the bottom of a ready-made graham cracker pie shell.
Mix up pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk instead of 2 cups. After mixing for 1 minute, place half of container of Cool Whip and continue mixing.
Pour into pie crust.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle the rest of peanut butter mixture on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion together in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add beaten eggs, milk, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put melted butter on the bottom of casserole dish; add squash mixture and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine carrots, broccoli, spinach, onion and all seasonings.
Add just enough water to prevent mixture from sticking.
Simmer for 30 minutes, or until all the liquid is absorbed.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil until tender; add meat and cook until no longer pink.
Drain well.
Season with paprika, chili powder and crushed red pepper to taste.
Stir well, add vegetables and soup.
Mix well; place in greased casserole and cover completely with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350 oven for 30 minutes.
Top each serving with a slice of cheese if desired.

title: oriental style steak
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add onions and green peppers. Saute about 2 minutes.
Add beef and sprinkle with garlic powder. After meat browns a little, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until meat is tender and sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and pat into 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.
